[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 1/100 path 3/5 answer="Let \\( x \\) represent the total number of vacuum cleaners Melanie started with. According to the problem:\n\n1. She sold \\(\\frac{1}{3}\\) of her vacuum cleaners at the green house, so she had \\(\\frac{x}{3}\\).\n2. She sold 2 more to the red house than she did to the green house, so she had \\(\\frac{x}{3} + 2\\).\n3. She kept half of what was left at the orange house, which is \\(\\frac{1}{2} \\times (\\frac{x}{3} + 2)\\).\n\nAfter all these sales, she has 5 vacuum cleaners left, so we can set up the equation:\n\\[ \\frac{x}{3} + 2 + \\frac{1}{2} \\times (\\frac{x}{3} + 2) = 5 \\]\n\nSolving this equation will give us the total number of vacuum cleaners Melanie started with. Let's do the calculation.\nFirst, simplify the second term:\n\\[ \\frac{1}{2} \\times (\\frac{x}{3} + 2) = \\frac{x}{4} + 1 \\]\n\nNow our equation looks like this:\n\\[ \\frac{x}{3} + 2 + \\frac{x}{4} + 1 = 5 \\]\nCombine like terms:\n\\[ \\frac{x}{3} + \\frac{x}{4} + 3 = 5 \\]\nTo combine these fractions, find a common denominator, which is 12:\n\\[ \\frac{4x}{12} + \\frac{3x}{12} + 3 = 5 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{7x}{12} + 3 = 5 \\]\nSubtract 3 from both sides:\n\\[ \\frac{7x}{12} = 2"
