[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 3/5 answer='First, calculate the number of kittens Patchy has:\nPatchy has had thrice the number of kittens as adopted ones, so Patchy has 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\n\nNext, we know Trixie has 12 kittens.\n\nFinally, add up all the kittens:\n21 (Patchy) + 12 (Trixie) = 33 kittens.\n\nTherefore, the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family now has is 33.'
