[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 5/5 answer="To determine the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family has now, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. Identify how many kittens Patchy has:\n   - Patchy has had thrice the number of kittens they initially had.\n   - They initially had 7 kittens.\n   - Therefore, Patchy has 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\n\n2. Identify how many kittens Trixie has:\n   - Trixie has had 12 kittens.\n\n3. Calculate the total number of kittens before the adoption of the second kitten (Patchy):\n   - Patchy + Trixie = 21 + 12 = 33 kittens.\n\n4. Add the newly adopted kittens to the initial count:\n   - Initial count of kittens: 7\n   - New kittens adopted: 21\n   - Total kittens = 7 + 21 = 28 kittens.\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has **28** kittens."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 done id=gsm8k_test_54 prediction='54' gold='40' correct=False vote_counts={'54': 1, '13': 1, 'First, calculate the number of kittens Patchy has:\nPatchy has had thrice the number of kittens as adopted ones, so Patchy has 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\n\nNext, we know Trixie has 12 kittens.\n\nFinally, add up all the kittens:\n21 (Patchy) + 12 (Trixie) = 33 kittens.\n\nTherefore, the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family now has is 33.': 1, '18': 1, "To determine the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family has now, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. Identify how many kittens Patchy has:\n   - Patchy has had thrice the number of kittens they initially had.\n   - They initially had 7 kittens.\n   - Therefore, Patchy has 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\n\n2. Identify how many kittens Trixie has:\n   - Trixie has had 12 kittens.\n\n3. Calculate the total number of kittens before the adoption of the second kitten (Patchy):\n   - Patchy + Trixie = 21 + 12 = 33 kittens.\n\n4. Add the newly adopted kittens to the initial count:\n   - Initial count of kittens: 7\n   - New kittens adopted: 21\n   - Total kittens = 7 + 21 = 28 kittens.\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has **28** kittens.": 1}
