[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 3/5 answer="To calculate the total hours Jim spends on both TV and reading over 4 weeks:\n\n1. First, let's determine how long Jim spends reading each day:\n   Reading time per session = Total TV time / Number of sessions\n   Reading time per session = 2 / 3 ≈ 0.6667 hours\n\n2. Since Jim goes to bed and reads for half as long every night, we multiply this daily reading time by 2:\n   Reading time per day = Reading time per session * 2\n   Reading time per day = 0.6667 * 2 = 1.3333 hours\n\n3. Now, we can find out how long he spends reading weekly (3 days):\n   Weekly reading time = Reading time per day * 3\n   Weekly reading time = 1.3333 * 3 ≈ 4.0000 hours\n\n4. Finally, we calculate his weekly total TV + reading spending:\n   Weekly total = TV time + Reading time per week\n   Weekly total = 2 + 4.0000 = 6.0000 hours\n\n5. To find the total for 4 weeks, we multiply the weekly total by 4:\n   Total weeks = 4 weeks\n   Total spending = Weekly total * Weeks\n   Total spending = 6.0000 * 4 = 24.0000 hours\n\nTherefore, Jim spends 24.0000 hours on both TV and reading in 4 weeks."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 4/5 answer="First, we calculate how long Jim spent reading each time:\nHalf of what he spends watching TV is 2 / 2 = 1 hour.\nHe repeats this process 3 times a week, so in one week, he spends 3 * 1 hour = 3 hours reading.\n\nOver the course of 4 weeks, he would spend 4 * 3 hours = 12 hours reading.\n\nNow, let's consider his time spent watching TV:\nHe spends 2 hours watching TV each time, so over 4 weeks, he spends 4 * 2 hours = 8 hours watching TV.\n\nAdding both amounts together gives us total spending:\n8 hours (watching TV) + 12 hours (reading) = 20 hours.\n\nTherefore, the total time Jim spends on TV and reading in 4 weeks is 20 hours."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 5/100 path 5/5 answer="First, let's determine how long Jim spends reading each time. Since he reads half as long as he watches TV, he reads:\n\n2 hours / 2 = <<2/2=1>>1 hour\n\nNow, since he goes to bed and reads for half as long each time (which is 1 hour), we multiply this time by 3 to get the total reading time over three nights:\n\n1 hour/night × 3 nights/week × 4 weeks = <<1*3*4=12>>12 hours\n\nFinally, to find out how many hours he spends on both TV and reading in one week, we add the two amounts together:\n\n12 hours (TV) + 12 hours (reading) = <<12+12=24>>24 hours\n\nTherefore, in four weeks, he spends a total of 24 hours on TV and reading."
