ads:\n\n2 hours / 2 = <<2/2=1>>1 hour\n\nNow, since he goes to bed and reads for half as long each time (which is 1 hour), we multiply this time by 3 to get the total reading time over three nights:\n\n1 hour/night × 3 nights/week × 4 weeks = <<1*3*4=12>>12 hours\n\nFinally, to find out how many hours he spends on both TV and reading in one week, we add the two amounts together:\n\n12 hours (TV) + 12 hours (reading) = <<12+12=24>>24 hours\n\nTherefore, in four weeks, he spends a total of 24 hours on TV and reading.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 6/100 start id=gsm8k_test_88
