[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 1/5 answer="First, let's find out how many photographs Jamal's phone can hold based on the information provided:\n\nJamal's phone holds 1800 photographs.\n\nIt's mentioned that Jamal's phone can hold 6 times more photographs than Brittany's phone. So we can calculate how many photographs Brittany's phone can hold like this:\n\n6 × 1800 photographs = 10800 photographs\n\nNow, Brittany's phone can hold up to 50 times more photographs than the number of birds in Jamal's photograph of the ducks at the zoo. We know that Jamal's phone holds 1800 photographs, so we can set up an equation to find out how many photographs Brittany's phone can hold:\n\nBrittany's phone photos + 50 × 1800 = Total photos Jamal's phone can hold\nLet B represent the number of photographs Brittany's phone can hold:\nB + 50 × 1800 = 1800\nB + 90000 = 1800\nB = 1800 - 90000\nB = -88200 (This negative value doesn't make sense because it's not possible)\n\nThis seems incorrect since we're dealing with actual photographs. Let's recheck our steps. \n\nIf we want to solve for B correctly:\n\nWe already know that Brittany's phone can hold 90000 photographs from Jamal's phone plus 50 × 1800 photographs from Jamal's phone:\n\n90000 photographs + 50 × 1800 = 1800 photographs\n90000 + 90000 = 1800\n180000 = 1800\n\nThis shows there was no mistake in the setup"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 2/5 answer="First, we find out how many photographs Jamal's phone can hold, which is 6 times the number of photographs Brittany's phone can hold. Since Jamal's phone holds 1800 photographs, we divide 1800 by 6 to get the number of photographs Brittany's phone can hold. This gives us:\n\\[ \\text{Brittany's photos} = \\frac{1800}{6} = 300 \\]\nNext, we know that Brittany's phone can hold up to 50 times more photographs than the number of birds in Jamal's photograph of the ducks at the zoo. So if Jamal's phone can hold 300 photographs, it means there are 300 × 50 = 15000 birds in Jamal's photograph."
