[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 4/5 answer="First, let's find out how many photographs Jamal's phone can hold. Since Jamal's phone can hold 6 times more photographs than Brittany's, we have:\nNumber of photographs in Jamal's phone = Number of photographs in Brittany's phone + 6\n\nWe know Jamal's phone can hold 1800 photographs, so:\n1800 = (Number of photographs in Brittany's phone) + 6\n1800 - 6 = Number of photographs in Brittany's phone\n1794 = Number of photographs in Brittany's phone\n\nNow, we know that Brittany's phone can hold up to 50 times more photographs than the number of birds in Jamal's photograph. We already calculated that Jamal's phone can hold 50 times the number of birds in her photograph, which was 1800 photographs. So:\n\nNumber of photographs in Brittany's phone = 50 × Number of birds in Jamal's photograph\nNumber of photographs in Brittany's phone = 50 × 1800\nNumber of photographs in Brittany's phone = 90,000\n\nTo find out how many ducks can be seen in the photograph, we divide the total number of photographs in the phone by the number of photographs each duck can hold. Each duck can hold 1 photograph:\n\nNumber of ducks = Total number of photographs ÷ Number of photographs per duck\nNumber of ducks = 90,000 ÷ 1\nNumber of ducks = 90,000\n\nSo, there would be 90,000 ducks in Jamal's photograph of ducks at the zoo if the conditions were met."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 8/100 path 5/5 answer="First, we find out how many photographs Jamal’s phone can hold: 1800 photos.\nIt holds 6 times more than Brittany's phone, so Brittany's phone can hold: 1800 ÷ 6 = <<1800/6=300>>300 photos.\nBrittany's phone could also hold 50 times more than the number of birds in Jamal's photo, meaning there are 50 × 1800 = <<50*1800=90000>>90,000 birds in her photo.\nSo, the number of ducks she was able to see is 90,000 (birds) divided by 2 (for each duck): 90,000 / 2 = <<90000/2=45,000>>45,000 ducks."
