imes (\\text{Hourly Rate}) \\]\nSubstituting in the numbers, we get:\n\\[ \\text{Weekly Earnings} = (2 \\, \\text{hours/day}) \\times (7 \\, \\text{days/week}) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Weekly Earnings} = 14 \\, \\text{dollars/week} \\]\nSo, Jordan would earn $14 in one week if he spent all his video game time working.': 1, "To calculate how much money Jordan would earn in one week, we'll first determine how much he spends on playing video games and work.\n\nJordan spends 2 hours playing video games each day. Since there are 7 days in a week, he spends:\n2 hours/day × 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, we can calculate his earnings from playing video games:\nEarnings from video games = Hours played/week × Hourly wage\nEarnings from video games = 14 hours/week ÷ 2 hours/hour\nEarnings from video games = $7/week\n\nThen, we multiply the earnings from video games by his hourly rate (which is 10 dollars per hour):\nWeekly earnings from working = Earnings from video games × Hourly wage\nWeekly earnings from working = $7/week × $10/hour\nWeekly earnings from working = $70/week\n\nSo, Jordan would earn $70 in one week if he worked all of his video game time.": 1, 'To calculate how much money Jordan would earn in one week, we first determine how many hours he spends on video games each day and then multiply that by the number of days in a week (assuming 7). \n\nJordan works 2 hours daily playing video games, so in one week (which has 7 days), he would work:\n\n2 hours/day * 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, we calculate his earnings from his jobs. Each hour he earns $10, so in one week (14 hours):\n\n14 hours/week * $10/hour = $140/week\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $140 in one week if he spent all his video game time working instead.': 1}
