[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 5/5 answer="Firstly, calculate the number of fish Anakin caught:\n- Starfish: 10\n- Sea Horses: 6\n- Clownfish: 3\n\nTotal fish caught by Anakin = 10 + 6 + 3 = 19\n\nLocsin caught:\n- 5 fewer starfish than Anakin: 10 - 5 = 5 stars\n- 3 fewer sea hores than Anakin: 6 - 3 = 3 seas\n- 2 more clownfish than Anakin: 3 - 2 = 1 clowns\n\nTotal fish caught by Locsin = 5 (stars) + 3 (seas) + 1 (clownfish) = 9\n\nNow, we sum up all the fish caught by both:\nAnakin's total = 19\nLocsin's total = 9\n\nCombined total = Anakin's total + Locsin's total = 19 + 9 = 28\n\nSo, Anakin and Locsin managed to catch 28 fish in total."
