[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 5/5 answer='To find out how much all the toys are worth, we first calculate the individual costs:\n\n- One red car costs $4.\n- A doll costs as much as 3 action figures, so each action figure costs $5 (since $4 / 3 = $5).\n- The total cost of the dolls is 3 * $5 = $<<3*5=15>>15.\n\nNow, we add up the total cost of all the toys:\nRed cars: $4\nDoll: $15\nAction figures: $5\n\n$4 + $15 + $5 = $<<4+15+5=24>>24\n\nSo, all the toys are worth $24 in total.'
