[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 14/100 path 1/5 answer='First, we find out how many crabs Monic has. Since Monic has 4 fewer crabs than Bo, and Bo has 40 crabs, Monic has 40 - 4 = 36 crabs.\n\nNext, we determine how many crabs Rani has. Rani has ten more crabs than Monic, so Rani has 36 + 10 = 46 crabs.\n\nFinally, to find the total number of crabs the three have together, we sum their individual amounts: 46 (Monic) + 36 (Rani) + 40 (Bo) = 122 crabs.\n\nSo, the total number of crabs the three have together is 122.'
