t of rides = Cost of food + (Number of rides × Cost per ride) = $15.75 + (2 × $33)\n\nNow, let's solve for the total cost of rides:\nTotal cost of rides = $15.75 + ($33 × 2)\nTotal cost of rides = $15.75 + $66\nTotal cost of rides = $81.75\n\nFinally, we divide the total cost of rides by the number of people (which is 3):\nAmount per person = Total cost of rides / Number of people = $81.75 / 3 = $27.25\n\nSo, each friend should pay $27.25.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 start id=gsm8k_test_191
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 1/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 1/5 answer='To determine how many pounds of insects each duck eats per day, we first calculate the weekly consumption for the entire flock:\n\nEach duck eats 3.5 pounds of insects per week, so together all ten ducks would consume:\n\\[ 10 \\times 3.5 = 35 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nNext, we need to find out how many pounds of insects one duck eats per day. We divide the total weekly consumption by the number of days in a week (which is 7):\n\n\\[ \\frac{35}{7} = 5 \\text{ pounds per day} \\]\n\nTherefore, each duck eats 5 pounds of insects per day.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 2/5 answer='5'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 3/5 answer='To find out how many pounds of insects the group of ten ducks need daily, we first calculate the weekly consumption:\n\nEach duck eats 3.5 pounds of insects per week.\n\nWith ten ducks, the total weekly consumption would be:\n10 ducks * 3.5 pounds/duck = 35 pounds/week\n\nNow we convert this to daily consumption since one week equals 7 days:\n35 pounds/week ÷ 7 days/week = 5 pounds/day\n\nTherefore, the ducks need 5 pounds of insects per day to survive.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 4/5 answer='To determine the amount of insects needed per day for a flock of ten ducks, we first need to calculate the total weekly insect consumption for the entire flock.\n\nEach duck eats 3.5 pounds of insects per week. Since there are 10 ducks in the flock, the total weekly insect consumption for the flocks would be:\n\n\\[ 10 \\text{ ducks} \\times 3.5 \\text{ pounds/duck/week} = 35 \\text{ pounds/week} \\]\n\nNext, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly insect consumption by 7 to find out how much it would cost in one day:\n\n\\[ 35 \\text{ pounds/week} \\div 7 \\text{ days/week} = 5 \\text{ pounds/day} \\]\n\nTherefore, the ducks need 5 pounds of insects per day.'
