[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 1/5 answer="Let's break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1. Initially, Elaine had 20 Pokemon cards.\n2. In the first month, she collected three times that amount:\n   Three times 20 = 60 cards\n\n3. In the second month, she collected 20 fewer cards than the first month:\n   Sixty - 20 = 40 cards\n\n4. In the third month, she collected twice the sum of the cards from the first two months:\n   (20 + 40) × 2 = 60 × 2 = 120 cards\n\nNow let's add up all the cards collected over the three months:\nInitial cards + First month + Second month + Third month = \n20 + 60 + 40 + 120 = 240 cards\n\nSo, Elaine now has a total of 240 Pokemon cards."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 2/5 answer="First, we calculate how many Pokémon cards Elaine collected each month:\n- First month: \\(3 \\times 20 = 60\\) cards\n- Second month: \\(20 - 20 = 0\\) cards (no additional cards collected)\n- Third month: \\(2 \\times (20 + 60) = 2 \\times 80 = 160\\) cards\n\nNow, let's sum up all the cards collected over the three months:\n\nTotal cards = Cards from first month + Cards from second month + Cards from third month\n\\(= 60 + 0 + 160\\)\n\nSo, the total number of cards is:\n\\(= 220\\) cards\n\nThus, Elaine has 220 Pokemon cards now in total."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 3/5 answer='First, we calculate the number of cards collected each month:\n- In the first month, she collected three times the number of cards as she originally had: 20 * 3 = 60 cards.\n- In the second month, she collected 20 fewer cards than the first month: 60 - 20 = 40 cards.\n- In the third month, she collected twice the combined number of cards from the first two months: (60 + 40) * 2 = 200 cards.\n\nNow, we add up all the cards collected over the three months:\n20 (initial) + 60 (first month) + 40 (second month) + 200 (third month) = 320 cards.\n\nSo, Elaine now has a total of 320 cards.'
