[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 18/100 path 4/5 answer="First, let's calculate how many kilometers Micheal rode in the first period (four weeks) where he rode 25 kilometers every time:\n\n4 weeks * 5 rides/week * 25 km/ride = 500 km\n\nNext, let's calculate his mileage during the second period (three weeks), where he rode 25 kilometers once a week for 60 kilometers each time:\n\n3 weeks * 2 rides/week * 60 km/ride = 360 km\n\nNow we can sum up all the distances:\n\nTotal distance = Distance from first period + Distance from second period\nTotal distance = 500 km + 360 km = 860 km\n\nSo, Michael rode a total of 860 kilometers over the two periods."
