[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 18/100 path 5/5 answer='For the first 4 weeks, Michael rode the bike 5 times a week, with each trip covering 25 kilometers:\n\\[ 5 \\text{ trips/week} \\times 25 \\text{ km/trip} = 125 \\text{ km/week} \\]\nOver 4 weeks, this totals to:\n\\[ 125 \\text{ km/week} \\times 4 \\text{ weeks} = 500 \\text{ km} \\]\n\nFor the next 3 weeks, he rode the bike 2 times a week, with each trip covering 60 kilometers:\n\\[ 2 \\text{ trips/week} \\times 60 \\text{ km/trip} = 120 \\text{ km/week} \\]\nOver these 3 weeks, this totals to:\n\\[ 120 \\text{ km/week} \\times 3 \\text{ weeks} = 360 \\text{ km} \\]\n\nTo find the total distance Michael covered over all three periods, we sum up the distances from both parts of his routine:\n\\[ 500 \\text{ km} + 360 \\text{ km} = 860 \\text{ km} \\]\n\nTherefore, the total number of kilometers Michael rode his bike is 860 kilometers.'
