[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 1/5 answer='First, we calculate how many pieces Kalinda can add per minute:\nKalinda at 4 pieces/minute\n\nHer mom adds half as many pieces per minute, so:\nMom at 4 / 2 = 2 pieces/minute\n\nTogether, they can add:\n4 + 2 = <<4+2=6>>6 pieces per minute\n\nWith 360 pieces total, it will take:\n360 / 6 = <<360/6=60>>60 minutes\n\nTo convert minutes into hours:\n60 minutes ÷ 60 minutes/hour = 1 hour\n\nTherefore, it will take them 1 hour to complete the puzzle.'
