[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 4/5 answer="To solve this problem, let's first determine how long it would take both Kalinda and her mom to finish the puzzle together:\n\nKalinda works at a rate of 4 pieces per minute.\nHer mom works at half that rate, so her mom's rate is 4 / 2 = 2 pieces per minute.\n\nTogether, they work at a combined rate of 4 + 2 = 6 pieces per minute.\n\nNow, we know there are 360 pieces in total. To find out how many minutes it takes for them to complete all the pieces together, we divide the total number of pieces by their combined rate:\n360 pieces / 6 pieces per minute = 60 minutes.\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we convert the time from minutes to hours:\n60 minutes ÷ 60 minutes/hour = 1 hour.\n\nTherefore, it will take them **1 hour** to complete the puzzle."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 5/5 answer="To calculate the time it takes to complete the puzzle, we first need to determine the rates at which each person works:\n\nKalinda's rate: 4 pieces per minute\n\nHer mom's rate: Half of Kalinda's rate, so 4 / 2 = 2 pieces per minute\n\nNow we know their combined rate: 4 (Kalinda) + 2 (Mom) = 6 pieces per minute\n\nNext, we divide the total number of puzzle pieces by their combined rate to find out how long it will take:\n\nTotal puzzle pieces = 360\nCombined rate = 6 pieces per minute\n\nTime taken = Total puzzle pieces / Combined rate\nTime taken = 360 / 6 = 60 minutes\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we convert the time to hours:\n\nTime in hours = Time taken in minutes / Minutes per hour\nTime in hours = 60 / 60 = 1 hour\n\nTherefore, it will take them 1 hour to complete the puzzle."
