 mom's rate: Half of Kalinda's rate, so 4 / 2 = 2 pieces per minute\n\nNow we know their combined rate: 4 (Kalinda) + 2 (Mom) = 6 pieces per minute\n\nNext, we divide the total number of puzzle pieces by their combined rate to find out how long it will take:\n\nTotal puzzle pieces = 360\nCombined rate = 6 pieces per minute\n\nTime taken = Total puzzle pieces / Combined rate\nTime taken = 360 / 6 = 60 minutes\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we convert the time to hours:\n\nTime in hours = Time taken in minutes / Minutes per hour\nTime in hours = 60 / 60 = 1 hour\n\nTherefore, it will take them 1 hour to complete the puzzle.": 1}
