nSimplify and solve for \\( x \\):\n\n\\[\nx + 5 - 7 + 8 = 20\n\\]\n\\[\nx + 6 = 20\n\\]\n\\[\nx = 20 - 6\n\\]\n\\[\nx = 14\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the initial number of people who got on the bus at the terminal is **14**.': 1, 'Let \\( x \\) represent the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal initially. We can set up the following equation based on the given information:\n\n\\( x + 5 + 7 - 8 = 20 \\)\n\nSimplifying the left side gives us:\n\n\\( x + 6 = 20 \\)\n\nSubtracting 6 from both sides gives us:\n\n\\( x = 14 \\)\n\nSo, the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal is 14.': 1}
