[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 28/100 path 1/5 answer="First, calculate the duration of each activity:\n1. Yoga class: 1 hour\n2. Cooking class: 3 * 1 hour (twice as long)\n3. Cheese-tasting event: 0.5 hour\n4. Museum tour: 0.5 hour (half as long as the cooking class)\n5. Errands: 2 hours\n\nNow sum up the durations to find the total time spent:\nTotal time = 1 + 3 * 1 + 0.5 + 0.5 + 2 = 1 + 3 + 1 + 0.5 + 2 = 7.5 hours\n\nTherefore, all of Peyton's after-work activities will take 7.5 hours."
