[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 28/100 path 3/5 answer="To find out how many hours all of Peyton's after-work activities will take, we'll first determine the duration of each activity:\n\n1. Yoga class: 1 hour\n2. Cooking class: 3 times as long as the yoga class, so 3 hours\n3. Cheese-tasting event: Half an hour\n4. Museum tour: Half as long as the cooking class, so 0.5 hours\n5. Errands: 2 hours\n\nNow, let's sum up these durations:\n\n1 + 3 + 0.5 + 2 = <<1+3+0.5+2=6.5>>6.5 hours\n\nTherefore, all of Peyton's after-work activities will take 6.5 hours total."
