[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 28/100 path 4/5 answer="First, calculate the duration of each activity:\n- Yoga class: 1 hour\n- Cooking class: 3 times as long as yoga, so 1 hour * 3 = 3 hours\n- Cheese-tasting event: Half an hour, so 0.5 hours\n- Museum tour: Half the time of the cooking class, so 3 hours / 2 = 1.5 hours\n- Errands: 2 hours\n\nNow sum up the durations:\n1 (yoga) + 3 (cooking) + 0.5 (cheese-tasting) + 1.5 (museum) + 2 = 9.5 hours\n\nTherefore, Peyton's after-work activities will take a total of 9.5 hours. The final answer is 9.5."
