[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 31/100 path 4/5 answer="First, we find out how many letters are in Indras' name:\nIndras' name has 6 letters.\n\nNext, we calculate half the number of letters in her name:\nHalf = 6 / 2 = <<6/2=3>>\n\nThen, we determine how many letters the sister's name has based on half of Indras' letters:\nSister's name = 3 + 4 = <<3+4=7>>\n\nFinally, we find the total number of letters in both names:\nTotal letters = Indras' name + Sister's name = 6 + 7 = <<6+7=13>>\n\nTherefore, Indras and her sister have a total of 13 letters in their names."
