[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 start id=gsm8k_test_432
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/5 answer='First, we calculate how many dragons Prince Arthur slayed:\nPrince Arthur slayed 3/4 * 100 dragons = 75 dragons.\n\nNext, we find out how many dragons Prince Walter slayed:\nPrince Walter slayed 2 * 75 dragons = 150 dragons.\n\nThen, we determine how many dragons Prince Bruce slayed:\nPrince Bruce slayed 1/5 * 150 dragons = 30 dragons.\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slayed 30 dragons.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/5 answer="First, let's find out how many dragons Prince Arthur slayed. Since Prince Arthur slew three-quarters as many dragons as Prince Thaddeus, we calculate:\n\nPrince Arthur's dragons slain = 100 dragons / 4 = 25 dragons\n\nNow, let's look at Prince Walter's dragon-slaying method. He slew twice as many dragons as Prince Arthur:\n\nPrince Walter's dragons slain = 25 dragons * 2 = 50 dragons\n\nFinally, Prince Bruce slew one-fifth as many dragons as Prince Walter using a nail file:\n\nPrince Bruce's dragons slain = 50 dragons / 5 = 10 dragons\n\nSo, Prince Bruce has slain 10 Dragons."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 3/5 answer='30'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 4/5 answer="First, let's calculate how many dragons each person slew:\n\n- Prince Thaddeus: He slew 100 dragons with his mighty sword.\n- Prince Arthur: Using a spear, he slew three quarters as many dragons as Prince Thaddeus. Therefore, he slew \\( \\frac{3}{4} \\times 100 = 75 \\) dragons using his spear.\n- Prince Walter: Using a rusty iron axe, he slew twice as many dragons as Prince Arthur. Since Prince Arthur slew 75 dragons, Prince Walter slew \\( 2 \\times 75 = 150 \\) dragons.\n- Prince Bruce: Using a nail file, he slew one-fifth as many dragons as Prince Walter. Since Prince Walter slew 150 dragons, Prince Bruce slew \\( \\frac{1}{5} \\times 150 = 30 \\) dragons.\n\nPrince Bruce has slain 30 dragons."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 5/5 answer='To find out how many dragons Prince Bruce killed, we first calculate the number of dragons each person killed:\n\nPrince Thaddeus killed 100 dragons.\n\nPrince Arthur killed three quarters (or 75%) of what Thaddeus killed:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Arthur} = \\frac{3}{4} \\times 100 = 75 \\]\n\nPrince Walter killed twice as many as Prince Arthur:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Walter} = 2 \\times 75 = 150 \\]\n\nPrince Bruce killed one-fifth (or 20%) of what Walter killed:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Bruce} = \\frac{1}{5} \\times 150 = 30 \\]\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce killed 30 dragons.'
