rince Bruce: Using a nail file, he slew one-fifth as many dragons as Prince Walter. Since Prince Walter slew 150 dragons, Prince Bruce slew \\( \\frac{1}{5} \\times 150 = 30 \\) dragons.\n\nPrince Bruce has slain 30 dragons.": 1, 'To find out how many dragons Prince Bruce killed, we first calculate the number of dragons each person killed:\n\nPrince Thaddeus killed 100 dragons.\n\nPrince Arthur killed three quarters (or 75%) of what Thaddeus killed:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Arthur} = \\frac{3}{4} \\times 100 = 75 \\]\n\nPrince Walter killed twice as many as Prince Arthur:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Walter} = 2 \\times 75 = 150 \\]\n\nPrince Bruce killed one-fifth (or 20%) of what Walter killed:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Bruce} = \\frac{1}{5} \\times 150 = 30 \\]\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce killed 30 dragons.': 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 33/100 start id=gsm8k_test_435
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 33/100 path 1/5 start
