[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 33/100 path 2/5 answer='Ray initially had 25 lollipops but kept 5 for himself. This leaves him with 25 - 5 = 20 lollipops to share with his four friends. \n\nTo find out how many lollipops each friend received, we divide the remaining lollipops by the number of friends:\n20 ÷ 4 = 5\n\nSo, each of his friends received 5 lollipops. The final answer is 5.'
