[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 33/100 path 5/5 answer="To solve this problem, we first calculate how many lollipops were given away among Ray’s friends. Since there are four friends sharing the remaining 5 lollipops, each friend received:\n\n5 ÷ 4 = 1 remainder 1\n\nSo each friend received one lollipop and had one lollipop left over because 4 × 1 = 4 lollipops were distributed.\n\nTherefore, each of Ray's friends received 1 lollipop."
