[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 start id=gsm8k_test_440
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 1/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 1/5 answer="To find the perimeter of the room, we first need to calculate the width using the area formula for a rectangle: Area = Length × Width. \n\nGiven:\nArea = 360 square feet\n\nLength = 3 yards = 18 feet (since there are 3 feet in a yard)\n\nUsing the area formula:\n\nWidth = Area ÷ Length\n   = 360 ÷ 18\n   = 20 feet\n\nNow, to get the perimeter, we can use the formula for the perimeter of a rectangle: Perimeter = 2 × (Length + Width).\n\nPerimeter = 2 × (18 + 20)\n         = 2 × 38\n         = 76 feet\n\nTherefore, the perimeter of Billie's rectangular bedroom is 76 feet."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 2/5 answer='246'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 3/5 start
