[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 34/100 path 4/5 answer="First, let's find the width of the room. We know the area (A) and the length (L), so we can use the formula for the area of a rectangle:\n\n\\[ A = L \\times W \\]\n\nGiven:\n\\( A = 360 \\) square feet\n\\( L = 3 \\) yards\n\nWe need to convert the length from yards to feet. Since there are 3 feet in a yard, \\( L \\) would be:\n\n\\( L_{\\text{feet}} = 3 \\text{ yards} \\times 3 \\frac{\\text{feet}}{\\text{yard}} = 9 \\text{ feet} \\)\n\nNow we can solve for the width \\( W \\):\n\n\\( 360 = 9 \\times W \\)\n\\( W = \\frac{360}{9} \\)\n\\( W = 40 \\) feet\n\nNext, we can calculate the perimeter \\( P \\) using the formula:\n\n\\[ P = 2 \\times (\\text{length} + \\text{width}) \\]\n\nSo:\n\n\\[ P = 2 \\times (3 \\text{ feet} + 40 \\text{ feet}) \\]\n\\[ P = 2 \\times 43 \\text{ feet} \\]\n\\[ P = 86 \\text{ feet} \\]\n\nTherefore, the perimeter of the room is 86 feet."
