**Cost Calculation**:\n   - Calculate the total cost for 170 balloons at the original price: \\( 170 \\times C \\).\n   - Calculate the total cost for 170 balloons at the increased price: \\( 170 \\times (C + 20) \\).\n   \n   The difference between these two amounts gives us the amount Bentley paid:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Amount paid} = 170 \\times (C + 20) - 170 \\times C\n   \\]\n   Simplifying this expression:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Amount paid} = 170C + 3400 - 170C = 3400\n   \\]\n\nSo, the amount Bentley paid to fill 170 balloons, considering the price increase, is $3400.": 1}
