[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 40/100 path 1/5 answer='First, we calculate the total number of cupcakes Mary can decorate with her 6 jars:\n\n\\( 6 \\text{ jars} \\times 8 \\text{ cupcakes/jar} = 48 \\text{ cupcakes} \\)\n\nNext, we determine how many pan holders are needed:\n\n\\( \\frac{48 \\text{ cupcakes}}{12 \\text{ cupcakes/panner}} = 4 \\text{ panners} \\)\n\nMary should bake 4 pan holders to have enough cupcakes for her to use up all of her sprinkles.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 40/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 40/100 path 2/5 answer='First, we calculate the total number of cupcakes Mary can decorate with her 6 jars of sprinkles:\n\nEach jar can decorate 8 cupcakes, so 6 jars can decorate:\n6 jars * 8 cupcakes/jar = 48 cupcakes\n\nMary wants to use up all of her sprinkles, which means she needs to bake enough cupcakes to get 48 cupcakes:\n\n48 cupcakes needed = 48 cupcakes\n\nNow, we determine how many pans of 12 cupcakes are required to make at least 48 cupcakes:\n\n48 cupcakes ÷ 12 cupcakes/pan = 4 pans\n\nSo, Mary should bake 4 pans worth of cupcakes.'
