[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 40/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 40/100 path 5/5 answer='First, we determine how many cupcakes Mary can decorate with one jar of sprinkles:\n\\[ \\text{Cupcakes per jar} = 8 \\]\n\nThen, since Mary has 6 jars, the total number of cupcakes she can decorate is:\n\\[ \\text{Total cupcakes} = 6 \\times 8 = 48 \\]\n\nNext, we calculate how many pans (each holding 12 cupcakes) she needs to bake to have at least 48 cupcakes:\n\\[ \\text{Number of pans needed} = \\frac{\\text{Total cupcakes}}{\\text{cupcakes per pan}} = \\frac{48}{12} = 4 \\]\n\nTherefore, Mary should bake **4 pans** worth of cupcakes to have enough to use up all of her sprinkles.'
