[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 41/100 path 3/5 answer='To find out how many books each child received, start by determining the total number of books Sarah bought. Given that she spent $300 and each book cost $15, we can calculate it like this:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total number of books} = \\frac{\\$300}{\\$15/\\text{book}} \\]\n\nCalculate the total number of books:\n\\[ \\text{Total number of books} = \\frac{300}{15} = 20 \\]\n\nNow, since she gave away these books equally among her 4 kids, divide the total number of books by the number of children:\n\\[ \\text{Number of books per child} = \\frac{20}{4} = 5 \\]\n\nSo, each child received 5 books.'
