[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 42/100 path 1/5 answer='First, calculate how many skeins of yarn Mariah and her grandma used:\n\nMariah used \\( \\frac{1}{4} \\) skein, and her grandma used \\( \\frac{1}{2} \\) skein. So together they used \\( \\frac{1}{4} + \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{1}{4} + \\frac{2}{4} = \\frac{3}{4} \\) skein.\n\nNow, since there are 364 yards in a skein of yarn, and they used \\( \\frac{3}{4} \\) of a skein, we multiply these amounts to find the total amount used:\n\n\\( \\frac{3}{4} \\times 364 = 279 \\) yards.\n\nSo, they used 279 yards of yarn altogether.'
