[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 43/100 path 5/5 answer="To determine how many popsicle sticks Frederick can make with his given budget and lumber types, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. **Determine the cost of each type of wood**:\n    - A 2 x 4 piece of wood costs $4.\n    - A 2 x 8 piece of wood costs $6.\n\n2. **Calculate the total number of sticks available from each type of wood**:\n    - For 2 x 4 pieces:\n        \\[\n        200 \\text{ (from a 2 x 4 piece)} \\div 4 = 50 \\text{ sticks}\n        \\]\n    - For 2 x 8 pieces:\n        \\[\n        400 \\text{ (from a 2 x 8 piece)} \\div 8 = 50 \\text{ sticks}\n        \\]\n\n3. **Identify the cheapest lumber**:\n    - Comparing the two options, both offer the same amount of wood:\n        - 2 x 4 pieces: $4\n        - 2 x 8 pieces: $6\n\n4. **Make the decision based on the cheaper option**:\n    - Since neither type of wood provides a significant advantage in terms of price or quantity compared to using one stick from either type, Frederick should choose to buy sticks from either the 2 x 4 or the 2 x 8 piece.\n\n5. **Calculate the maximum number of sticks Frederick can make**:\n    - Using the 2 x 4 piece wood:\n        \\[\n        200 \\text{ sticks} \\div 4 = 50 \\text{ sticks}\n        \\]\n    - Using the 2 x 8 piece wood:\n        \\[\n        400 \\text{ sticks} \\div 8 = 50 \\text{ sticks}"
