[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 47/100 path 2/5 answer='Let\'s break down the problem:\n\n1. First, we know that Elise writes the entire alphabet twice (one time as "A" and one time as "Z").\n2. Then, she writes half of the alphabet once, which is writing the letters "AB". So, she writes "AB" once.\n3. Finally, she rewrites everything she has already written. Since she wrote "AB" once, she will rewrite "AB" again.\n\nTo find out how many letters she has written in total:\n1. Write the entire alphabet twice: 2 times A, 2 times Z.\n2. Write half of the alphabet once: 5 times B.\n3. Rewrite the previously written letters again: 1 additional letter from what was rewritten (since she didn\'t write anything else).\n\nSo, we have:\n- Total letters written so far: 2 + 5 + 1 = 8 letters.\n- Additional letters written: 1 time each of B and A, which totals 2 times B.\n\nTherefore, the total number of letters Elise has written is 8 + 2 = 10 letters.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 47/100 path 3/5 start
