[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 2/5 answer='To find the initial weight, we can subtract the total weight loss over the 3-month period from his final weight. \n\nGiven:\n- Weight loss per month = 10 pounds\n- Number of months = 3\n\nWeight loss over 3 months = 10 pounds/month * 3 months = 30 pounds\n\nIf his final weight was 70 pounds, his initial weight would have been:\n\nInitial weight (initial weight before losing weight) = Final weight + Weight loss\nInitial weight (before losing weight) = 70 pounds + 30 pounds = 100 pounds\n\nSo, his initial weight was 100 pounds.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 3/5 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can work backwards from his final weight. Initially, he had 70 pounds at the end of 3 months. During these 3 months, he lost 10 pounds each month. So, before losing any weight, his initial weight would have been:\n\nInitial weight + (Weight lost per month × Number of months) = Final weight\n\nSo, initially:\n\n(10 pounds/month × 3 months) + Initial weight = 70 pounds\n\nNow, let's solve for the initial weight:\n\n30 pounds + Initial weight = 70 pounds\n\nThen subtract 30 pounds from both sides:\n\nInitial weight = 70 pounds - 30 pounds = 40 pounds\n\nTherefore, Mark's initial weight was 40 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 4/5 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can subtract the total weight loss over the three months from his final weight. \n\nHe lost 10 pounds per month for 3 months:\nTotal weight loss = 10 pounds/month * 3 months\n\nWe know his final weight:\nFinal weight = Initial weight - Total weight loss\n\nGiven:\nFinal weight = 70 pounds\n\nSo:\n10 × 3 = 30 pounds\nInitial weight = Final weight - Total weight loss\nInitial weight = 70 pounds - 30 pounds\n\nNow, let's calculate:\nInitial weight = 70 pounds - 30 pounds = 40 pounds\n\nMark's initial weight was 40 pounds."
