[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 1/5 answer='First, calculate the earnings from selling above $1000: $2500 - $1000 = $1500.\nThen add the first 10% commission for sales up to $1000: $1500 * 0.10 = $150.\nFinally, add the second 10% commission for the remaining $150: $150 + $150 = $300.\n\nSo, Antonella earned a total of $300.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 2/5 answer='1100'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 3/5 answer='2150'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 4/5 answer="First, calculate Antonella's earnings without any sales discount or commissions. For a sale worth $2500, she would earn:\n$2500 * 30% = $750.\n\nNext, since the total sales exceed $1000, she gets an additional 10% commission on top of the 30%. So, for the excess sales (i.e., $2500 - $1000), she would earn:\n$2500 * 10% = $250.\n\nFinally, sum up both parts to find out how much she earned in total:\n$750 + $250 = $1000.\n\nTherefore, the amount of money Antonella earned is $1000."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 5/5 answer="To calculate Antonella's earnings from selling goods worth $2500 with commissions, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Calculate the initial commission:** Since the sale was under $1000, she gets 30% commission on $1000.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Commission} = 1000 \\times 0.30 = 300\n   \\]\n\n2. **Calculate the additional commission:** For sales over $1000, she gets an additional 10% commission on the remaining amount ($2500 - $1000).\n   \\[\n   \\text{Additional Commission} = (2500 - 1000) \\times 0.10 = 1500 \\times 0.10 = 150\n   \\]\n\n3. **Total Commission Earned:** Add both components together to find the total commission.\n   \\[\n   \\text{Total Commission} = 300 + 150 = 450\n   \\]\n\nTherefore, Antonella earned $450 in total commission from selling goods worth $2500."
