oots cost $16 and there's a shipping fee of $4. So, the total cost on Amazon is:\n\\[ 16 + 4 = 20 \\]\n\nOn eBay, the boots cost $13 and there's also a shipping fee of twice the amount on Amazon (since it's twice as much). Therefore, the shipping fee is $4 * 2 = $8. So, the total cost on eBay is:\n\\[ 13 + 8 = 21 \\]\n\nNow, to find out how much more expensive the boots are on eBay, we subtract the cost from Amazon from the cost on eBay:\n\\[ 21 - 20 = 1 \\]\n\nSo, the boots are 1 dollar more expensive on eBay than they are on Amazon.": 1, "First, let's calculate the total cost of the boots at both Amazon and eBay:\n\nOn Amazon:\n- Cost of boots: $16\n- Shipping: $4\nTotal cost on Amazon: $16 + $4 = $20\n\nOn eBay:\n- Cost of boots: $13\n- Shipping: Twice as much as Amazon, so $4 * 2 = $8\nTotal cost on eBay: $13 + $8 = $21\n\nNow we compare the total costs to find out how much more expensive they are on eBay:\n\n$21 (Ebay) - $20 (Amazon) = $1 more per item\n\nTherefore, the boots cost $1 more on eBay than on Amazon.": 1, "To compare the prices at Amazon and eBay, we'll first calculate the total cost of the boots at each place:\n\nAt Amazon:\nCost of boots = $16\nShipping = $4\nTotal cost at Amazon = Cost of boots + Shipping\nTotal cost at Amazon = $16 + $4 = $20\n\nAt eBay:\nCost of boots = $13\nShipping (twice as much as Amazon) = $4 * 2 = $8\nTotal cost at eBay = Cost of boots + Shipping\nTotal cost at eBay = $13 + $8 = $21\n\nNow, let's find out how much more expensive the boots are on eBay compared to Amazon:\nEarnings difference = Total cost at eBay - Total cost at Amazon\nEarnings difference = $21 - $20 = $1\n\nTherefore, the boots would be $1 more expensive on eBay compared to when bought from Amazon.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 53/100 start id=gsm8k_test_600
