[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 53/100 path 1/5 answer="First, let's determine how much weight Jamaal used before increasing it by 50%.\n\nHe started with 8 pounds and increased it by 50%, which means:\n\\[ 8 \\times (1 + 50\\%) = 8 \\times 1.5 = 12 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nNow, we increase this weight by 2 pounds to find out what he used after increasing it:\n\\[ 12 + 2 = 14 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo, the weight that Jamaal now uses is 14 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 53/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 53/100 path 2/5 answer='First, we calculate how much heavier he used the original 8-pound weight by:\n8 pound increase = 8 + (8 * 0.5) = 8 + 4 = 12 pounds\n\nNow, if he decides to use a weight two pounds lighter than the increased amount, his new weight would be:\n12 - 2 = 10 pounds\n\nSo, the weight he now uses is 10 pounds.'
