[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 54/100 path 1/5 answer='First, we find out how old Steve\'s wife was when he was born. Since his wife is 4 years older than him, she was 60 + 4 = 64 years old when Steve was born. Now, let\'s determine the ages of each individual:\n\n1. Steve is 60 years old.\n2. Steve\'s wife was 64 years old when Steve was born.\n3. Steve\'s son is half as old as his mom. So, the son\'s age is 60 / 2 = 30 years old.\n4. Steve\'s wife\'s current age is 64 years old (Steve\'s birth year).\n\nNow, we calculate the difference between the ages of the son\'s wife and his mother:\n- Mother\'s age: 64 years\n- Son\'s wife\'s age: 64 years\n\nTherefore, the difference between the ages of the son\'s wife and his mother is 64 - 64 = 0 years. However, since the question asks for "the" age of the son\'s wife, and no specific reference to "his" wife was provided earlier, it seems there might have been a misunderstanding or error in the initial question setup. If we were to strictly follow the given information, neither son\'s wife nor her husband would know the exact age difference without additional context about who they\'re talking about. If you meant to ask something else, please clarify.'
