[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 54/100 path 2/5 answer="First, we find out how old Steve's wife is. Since she is 4 years older than Steve, she is 60 + 4 = 64 years old.\nTheir son is currently half as old as his mom, so he is 60 / 2 = 30 years old.\nTheir son's wife is 3 years younger than her husband, so she is 30 - 3 = 27 years old."
