[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 55/100 path 1/5 answer="First, calculate the distance Alisa biked using the formula:\n\\[ \\text{Distance} = \\text{Speed} \\times \\text{Time} \\]\nAlisa's distance = \\( 12 \\, \\text{miles/hour} \\times 4.5 \\, \\text{hours} = 54 \\, \\text{miles} \\)\n\nNext, calculate the distance Stanley biked similarly:\n\\[ \\text{Distance} = \\text{Speed} \\times \\text{Time} \\]\nStanley's distance = \\( 10 \\, \\text{miles/hour} \\times 2.5 \\, \\text{hours} = 25 \\, \\text{miles} \\)\n\nNow, add both distances together to find the total distance they both biked:\n\\[ \\text{Total Distance} = \\text{Alisa's Distance} + \\text{Stanley's Distance} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Total Distance} = 54 \\, \\text{miles} + 25 \\, \\text{miles} = 79 \\, \\text{miles} \\]\n\nSo, Alisa and Stanley biked a total of 79 miles."
