[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 55/100 path 4/5 answer="To find out how far each person biked, we multiply their speed (in miles per hour) by the time they spent biking (in hours).\n\nAlisa's distance = Speed × Time = 12 mph × 4.5 hours = 54 miles\n\nStanley's distance = Speed × Time = 10 mph × 2.5 hours = 25 miles\n\nNow, to find out how many miles both biked together:\n\nTotal distance = Alisa's distance + Stanley's distance = 54 miles + 25 miles = 79 miles\n\nSo, Alisa and Stanley biked a total of 79 miles together."
