[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 57/100 path 3/5 answer='First, calculate the total cost of the candies. Since the candies cost $3.20 and there are 4 of them, the cost of one candy is $3.20 / 4 = $0.80.\nNext, calculate the total cost of the lollipops. Since Manolo bought 5 lollipops at $0.40 each, the cost of one lollipop is $0.40, so 5 lollipops cost 5 * $0.40 = $<<5*.40=2>>2.\nNow, find out the total cost of both candies and lollipops. That would be $3.20 (costs of candies) + $2 (costs of lollipops) = $5.20.\nFinally, find the total cost of 10 lollipops and 10 candies. That would be $5.20 (total cost of candies) + $10 (total cost of lollipops) = $15.20.\nTherefore, 10 lollipops and 10 candies will cost $15.20.'
