 lollipops * Cost per lollipop = 5 * $0.40\n\nFor the candies:\nNumber of candies = 4\nCost of one candy = $3.20\nTotal cost for candies = Number of candies * Cost per candy\n\nNow, let's calculate:\n\nTotal cost for lollipops = 5 * $0.40 = $<<5*0.40=2>>2\nTotal cost for candies = 4 * $3.20 = $<<4*3.20=12.80>>\n\nFinally, we'll add the two amounts together to get the total cost for 10 lollipops and 10 candies:\n\nTotal cost = Total cost for lollipops + Total cost for candies\nTotal cost = $2 + $12.80 = $<<2+12.80=14.80>>\n\nSo, 10 lollipops and 10 candies would cost Manolo $14.80.": 1}
