[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 1/5 answer="First, we calculate how many points Betty collected: \n- Adam had 50 points,\n- Betty collected 30% more than Adam, so \\(50 \\times (1 + 0.30) = 50 \\times 1.30 = 65\\).\n- Martha collected 3 times more points than Tom, so \\(30 \\times 3 = 90\\) points.\n- Tom had 30 points less than Betty, so \\(65 - 30 = 35\\) points.\n\nNow, let's find out how many total points the students have:\nAdam: 50\nBetty: 65\nMartha: 90\nTom: 35\n\nAdding these up gives us a total of 230 points.\n\nTo determine how many more points are needed, we subtract the minimum required points from the current total:\n\\[230 - 400 = -170\\]\n\nSince this result doesn't make sense in terms of positive points, it indicates there might have been an error in the initial calculation. Let's correct it:\n\n1. Adam: 50 points\n2. Betty: 65 points (30% more than Adam)\n3. Martha: 90 points (3 times more than Tom)\n4. Tom: 35 points (less than Betty)\n\nTotal points: \\(50 + 65 + 90 + 35 = 230\\)\n\nMin. Points Required: 400\n\nSince the corrected calculations show that the class currently has 230 points, which is already above the required 400 points, there isn't enough money to meet the requirement.\n\nTherefore, no additional points are needed because the budget is exceeded. The class would not qualify for the trip since they"
