[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 4/5 answer="To solve this problem, we'll start with the information given:\n\n1. Adam has collected 50 points.\n2. Betty collected 30% more than Adam.\n3. Marta collected 3 times the amount Betty collected.\n4. Tom has 30 points less than Betty.\n5. The minimum required number of points to go on the trip is 400 points.\n\nLet's calculate the points each student has based on the given information:\n\n1. Adam has 50 points.\n2. Betty collected 30% more than Adam:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Betty's points} = 50 + (0.30 \\times 50) = 50 + 15 = 65 \\text{ points}\n   \\]\n3. Marta collected 3 times the amount Betty collected:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Marta's points} = 3 \\times 65 = 195 \\text{ points}\n   \\]\n\nNow let's find out how many points are needed to reach the minimum required score:\n\\[\n\\text{Minimum score needed} = 400 \\text{ points}\n\\]\n\nTo find the points that remain unsatisfied, we subtract the minimum score from the current total:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Points remaining} = 400 - (\\text{Adam's points} + \\text{Betty's points} + \\text{Marta's points}) = 400 - (50 + 65 + 195)\n\\]\n\n\\[\n\\text{Points remaining} = 400 - 210 = 190 \\text{ points}\n\\]\n\nTherefore, the class needs **190 points** to meet the minimum requirement for the trip."
