[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 63/100 path 1/5 answer="To determine how much money the vendor saves a week, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. **Calculate daily savings**:\n    - Current price per tomato: $0.50\n    - New price per tomato: $0.40\n    - Daily number of tomatoes bought: 500\n\n   First, find out how many tomatoes can be purchased with the current price:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Tomatoes per day} = \\frac{\\text{Current price}}{\\text{Price per tomato}} = \\frac{0.50}{0.40}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Determine the difference between the two prices**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Difference} = \\text{New price per tomato} - \\text{Current price per tomato}\n   \\]\n   Using our previous calculations from step 1:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Difference} = \\frac{0.40}{0.40} - \\frac{0.50}{0.40}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Simplify the fractions**:\n   \\[\n   \\frac{0.40}{0.40} = 1\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   \\frac{0.50}{0.40} = \\frac{5}{4}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Subtract the differences**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Daily savings} = 1 - \\frac{5}{4}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Convert the subtraction to a simpler fraction form** (since \\(1\\) can be written as \\(\\frac{4}{4}\\)):\n   \\[\n   1 - \\frac{5}{4} = \\frac{4}{4} - \\frac{5}{4} = \\frac{-1}{4}\n   \\]\n\n6"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 63/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 63/100 path 2/5 answer='128.57'
