[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 start id=gsm8k_test_758
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 1/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 1/5 answer="First, let's find the amount of the discount using the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Discount} = \\text{Original Price} \\times \\frac{\\text{Discount Rate}}{100} \\]\n\nFor this problem:\n\\[ \\text{Discount} = 140 \\times \\frac{5}{100} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Discount} = 140 \\times 0.05 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Discount} = 7 \\]\n\nNow we subtract the discount from the original price to get the final price:\n\\[ \\text{Final Price} = 140 - 7 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Final Price} = 133 \\]\n\nSo, if the bag was marked $140 and with a 5% discount, you would have to pay $133 after the discount."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 2/5 answer='To find out how much you will pay after a 5% discount on a marked price, we first calculate the amount of the discount:\n\nDiscount amount = Marked price × Discount percentage\n                 = $140 × 0.05\n                 = $7\n\nNow, subtract the discount from the marked price to find your final price:\n\nFinal price = Marked price - Discount amount\n              = $140 - $7\n              = $133\n\nSo, after the discount, you will pay $133. The final answer is $133.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 3/5 answer='First, calculate the amount after applying the 5% discount on the original price:\nOriginal price: $140\nDiscount rate: 5%\nAmount with discount: Original price × (1 - Discount Rate) = $140 × (1 - 0.05) = $140 × 0.95 = $133\n\nTherefore, you will pay $133 after the discount.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 4/5 answer='133'
