[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 5/5 answer='To calculate the price after the discount, we first find the original price before the discount is applied (which is $140). Then, we apply the 5% discount on this amount ($140 multiplied by 5%). This can be calculated using the formula:\n\nPrice after discount = Original price × (Discount rate)\n\nSo, we calculate:\n$140 × 0.05 = $7\n\nTherefore, you would pay $7 less than the marked price.\n\nAnswer: You will pay $7 after the discount.'
