[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 65/100 path 2/5 answer='To determine how many additional wheels Henry needs, we first calculate the total number of wheels required for the cars and motorcycles separately:\n\nFor cars:\n57 cars * 4 wheels/car = <<57*4=228>>228 wheels\n\nFor motorcycles:\n73 motorcycles * 2 wheels/motorcycle = <<73*2=146>>146 wheels\n\nNow, sum up these values to get the total number of wheels needed:\n228 wheels + 146 wheels = <<228+146=374>>374 wheels\n\nHenry already has 650 wheels in his box. To find out how many more wheels he needs, subtract the number of wheels he already has from the total number he needs:\n374 wheels - 650 wheels = <<374-650=-276>>-276 wheels\n\nSince Henry cannot have negative wheels, this indicates there might be an error in the question or calculation. Please double-check the information provided. If the total number of wheels available exceeds the total required, Henry would indeed need to borrow or exchange one wheel from another toy set to ensure he meets his goal.'
