[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 1/5 answer='First, calculate the cost for each type of fruit:\n\nFor peaches:\nCost = Number of pounds × Price per pound\nCost = 6 pounds × $2.00/pound = $12.00\n\nFor plums:\nCost = 8 pounds × $1.00/pound = $8.00\n\nFor apricots:\nCost = 6 pounds × $3.00/pound = $18.00\n\nNow, sum up the total cost:\nTotal cost = Cost of peaches + Cost of plums + Cost of apricots\nTotal cost = $12.00 + $8.00 + $18.00 = $38.00\n\nTherefore, Winston spent $38.00 on his fruit picking.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 2/5 answer='First, we calculate the cost of each type of fruit that Winston picked:\n- Peaches: 6 pounds at $2.00 per pound = $2.00 x 6 = $<<2.00*6=12>>12\n- Plums: 8 pounds at $1.00 per pound = $1.00 x 8 = $<<1.00*8=8>>8\n- Apricots: 6 pounds at $3.00 per pound = $3.00 x 6 = $<<3.00*6=18>>18\n\nNext, we add up the total cost of all the fruits:\nTotal cost = Cost of peaches + Cost of plums + Cost of apricots\nTotal cost = $12 + $8 + $18 = $<<12+8+18=48>>48\n\nTherefore, Winston spent $48 on fruit.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 3/5 answer='Winston spent 6 * $2.00 = $<<6*2=12>>12 on peaches.\nHe spent 8 * $1.00 = $<<8*1=8>>8 on plums.\nAnd he spent 6 * $3.00 = $<<6*3=18>>18 on apricots.\nTherefore, the total amount he spent was $12 + $8 + $18 = $<<12+8+18=38>>38.'
