 plums: 8 pounds × $1.00/pound = $8.00\n- Pounds of apricots: 6 pounds × $3.00/pound = $18.00\n\nNow we sum up these amounts to find the total cost:\n\n$12.00 (peaches) + $8.00 (plums) + $18.00 (apricots) = $38.00\n\nTherefore, Winston spent $38.00 on his fruit.': 1}
