[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 2/5 answer='First, calculate the number of green cars:\nGreen cars = Red cars - 2 = 12 - 2 = 10\n\nThen, calculate the number of blue cars:\nBlue cars = Green cars * Number of blue cars per green car = 10 * 3 = 30\n\nNow, find out the total number of green, blue, and red cars:\nTotal (green + blue + red) = 10 + 30 + 12 = 52\n\nFinally, subtract this total from the overall number of cars in the rink to find the number of yellow cars:\nYellow cars = Total cars - Total (green + blue + red) = 75 - 52 = 23\n\nSo, the number of yellow cars is 23.'
