[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 done id=gsm8k_test_865 prediction='23' gold='23' correct=True vote_counts={'23': 1, 'First, calculate the number of green cars:\nGreen cars = Red cars - 2 = 12 - 2 = 10\n\nThen, calculate the number of blue cars:\nBlue cars = Green cars * Number of blue cars per green car = 10 * 3 = 30\n\nNow, find out the total number of green, blue, and red cars:\nTotal (green + blue + red) = 10 + 30 + 12 = 52\n\nFinally, subtract this total from the overall number of cars in the rink to find the number of yellow cars:\nYellow cars = Total cars - Total (green + blue + red) = 75 - 52 = 23\n\nSo, the number of yellow cars is 23.': 1, '53': 1, '43': 1, '52': 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 start id=gsm8k_test_919
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 1/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 1/5 answer='To find out how much money the class raised from selling lollipops, we first calculate the total number of lollipops sold:\n\\[ \\text{Total Lollipops Sold} = 30 \\text{ students} \\times 10 \\text{ lollipops/student} = 300 \\text{ lollipops} \\]\n\nNext, we calculate the profit made from selling these lollipops:\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = \\text{Total Lollipops Sold} \\times (\\text{Cost Per Lollipop} - \\text{Bargain Price}) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = 300 \\text{ lollipops} \\times (0.8 \\text{ dollars/lollypop} - 0.5 \\text{ dollars/lollypop}) \\]\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = 300 \\text{ lollipops} \\times 0.3 \\text{ dollars/lollypop} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = 90 \\text{ dollars} \\]\n\nFinally, we determine how much money the class raised:\n\\[ \\text{Total Money Raised} = \\text{Profit} + \\text{Bargain Price} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Total Money Raised} = 90 \\text{ dollars} + 0.5 \\text{ dollars} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Total Money Raised} = 90.5 \\text{ dollars} \\]\n\nSo, the class was able to raise $90.50 from selling lollipops.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 2/5 answer='0'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 3/5 answer="First, we calculate the total revenue from selling lollipops. Each student sold 10 lollipops at $0.8 each, so:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total Revenue} = 10 \\times 10 \\times \\$0.8 \\]\n\nNext, since there were 30 students and they bought each lollipop for $0.5, the profit made on each lollipop (before sales tax) is $0.5 minus $0.8 because both prices have been deducted:\n\n\\[ \\text{Profit per Lollipop} = \\$0.5 - \\$0.8 \\]\n\nNow, if we multiply the total revenue by the number of lollipops sold to find out how much money was raised from the profit of selling lollipops:\n\n\\[ \\text{Money Raised} = (\\text{Total Revenue}) \\times (\\text{Number of Students}) \\times (\\text{Lollipops Sold per Student}) \\]\n\nLet's do the math:\n\\[ \\text{Total Revenue} = 10 \\times 10 \\times \\$0.8 = \\$80 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Profit per Lollipop} = \\$0.5 - \\$0.8 = -\\$0.3 \\] (Note: This negative value indicates a loss rather than profit.) Since it's unlikely you'd lose money on such an operation, let's assume it's actually a gain for simplicity).\n\n\\[ \\text{Money Raised} = \\$80 \\times 30 \\times 10 = \\$24,000 \\]"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 4/5 answer='To calculate the total revenue from selling lollipop units, we multiply the number of students by the number of lollipops each student sells:\n\nTotal revenue = Number of students × Number of lollipops per student\nTotal revenue = 30 × 10\nTotal revenue = 300\n\nEach lollipop costs $0.8, so to find the total sales revenue, we multiply the total revenue by the price per lollipop:\n\nTotal sales revenue = Total revenue × Price per lollipop\nTotal sales revenue = 300 × 0.8\nTotal sales revenue = $240\n\nTo calculate the amount raised from buying the lollipops at a cost of $0.5 per unit, we multiply the total sales revenue by the cost per unit:\n\nMoney raised from buying lollipops = Total sales revenue × Cost per lollipop\nMoney raised from buying lollipops = $240 × 0.5\nMoney raised from buying lollipops = $120\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $120 from selling lollipops.'
