[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 1/5 answer='To find the average number of June bugs removed per day, we first need to calculate the total number of June bugs removed from Monday through Friday:\n\nMonday: 39 Junebugs\nTuesday and Wednesday: Twice as many as Monday, so 39 * 2 = 78 Junebugs\nThursday: 48 Junebugs\nFriday: 57 Junebugs\n\nAdding these together gives us the total:\n39 + 78 + 48 + 57 = 212 Junebugs removed\n\nNow, to find the average, we divide the total by the number of days (which is 4):\n\nAverage = Total / Number of days\nAverage = 212 / 4\nAverage = 53 Junebugs per day\n\nSo, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 53.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/5 answer="First, let's calculate the total number of Junebugs removed over the week:\n\nOn Monday: 39 Junebugs\nOn Tuesday and Wednesday combined (twice as many as Monday): \\(2 \\times 39 = 78\\) Junebugs\n\nAdding these together gives us \\(39 + 78 = 117\\) Junebugs removed so far.\n\nNow, we'll add the number of Junebugs removed each day from Thursday to Friday:\n\nThursday: 48 Junebugs\nFriday: 57 Junebugs\n\nTotal: \\(48 + 57 = 105\\) Junebugs removed.\n\nTo find the average number of Junebugs removed per day, we divide the total number of Junebugs by the number of days:\n\n\\(105 \\div 5 = 21\\)\n\nSo, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 21."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 3/5 answer='First, calculate the total number of Junebugs removed from Monday through Thursday:\n- Monday: 39 bugs\n- Tuesday: 2 * 39 = 78 bugs (since she removed twice as many as Monday)\n- Wednesday: 2 * 78 = 156 bugs\n- Thursday: 48 bugs\n- Friday: 57 bugs\n\nTotal removed so far: 39 + 78 + 156 + 48 + 57 = 378 bugs\n\nOn Friday, she removed 57 bugs. Now add these all together to get the total removals over four days:\n378 (total so far) + 57 = 435 bugs\n\nTo find the average number of bugs removed per day, divide the total by the number of days:\n435 / 4 = 108.75 bugs/day\n\nThe average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 108.75.'
