[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 77/100 path 1/5 answer='To find out how many loaves of bread the bakery has, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. First, calculate what 7 times the number of loaves Sam originally had would be:\n   7 * 70 = 490\n\n2. Then, subtract the 40 fewer loaves than that amount from the original total:\n   490 - 40 = 450\n\nSo, the bakery has **450** loaves of bread.'
