[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 77/100 path 2/5 answer="To find out how many loaves of bread the bakery has, we can set up an equation based on the information given:\n\nLet \\( S \\) represent the number of loaves of bread Sam originally had.\n\nAccording to the problem:\n\\[ S = 7S - 40 \\]\n\nWe know \\( S = 75 \\) (since the bakery has 40 less than seven times as many loaves of bread as Sam had last Friday).\n\nNow substitute the known value into the equation:\n\n\\[ 75 = 7(75) - 40 \\]\n\nCalculate the right side:\n\n\\[ 75 = 525 - 40 \\]\n\n\\[ 75 = 485 \\]\n\nOops! There seems to be a mistake in the calculation. Let's correct it and solve the equation again:\n\nStarting from the equation:\n\n\\[ 75 = 7(75) - 40 \\]\n\n\\[ 75 = 525 - 40 \\]\n\n\\[ 75 = 485 \\]\n\nIt appears there was an error in setting up the equation or solving it correctly. Let's re-evaluate with the correct approach:\n\nSince the bakery has 40 less than seven times as many loaves as Sam had last Friday, we can express this relationship directly:\n\n\\[ \\text{Bakery} = 7 \\times (\\text{Sam}) - 40 \\]\n\nGiven that Sam had 75 loaves last Friday, we can now calculate the number of loaves the bakery has:\n\n\\[ \\text{Bakery} = 7 \\times 75 - 40 \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Bakery} = 525 - 40 \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Bakery} = 485 \\]\n\nSo, the bakery has"
