[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 77/100 path 4/5 answer='First, calculate seven times the number of loaves Sam had last Friday. That would be 7 * 70 = <<7*70=490>>490 loaves.\nNext, add ten to get the total number of loaves the bakery has. This would be 490 + 40 = <<490+40=530>>530 loaves.\nTherefore, the bakery has 530 loaves of bread.'
