[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 1/5 answer="We start with the information given:\n1. Mike is 24 years old.\n2. Martha is 4 years younger than Mike. Therefore, Martha's age is \\(24 - 4\\).\n3. Jeff is 10 years older than Martha. To find Jeff's age, we subtract 10 from the age of Martha.\n\nLet's calculate each age step-by-step:\n\n1. **Mike's Age**: \\(24\\) years old.\n2. **Martha's Age**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Martha's Age} = \\text{Mike's Age} - 4 = 24 - 4 = 20 \\text{ years old}\n   \\]\n3. **Jeff's Age**:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Jeff's Age} = \\text{Martha's Age} - 10 = 20 - 10 = 10 \\text{ years old}\n   \\]\n\nSo, Jeff is currently 10 years old."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 2/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 2/5 answer="To find out Jeff's age, we can break down the relationships step by step:\n\n1. **Martha's Age**: Since Martha is 4 years younger than Mike, we can calculate Martha's age as follows:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Martha's age} = \\text{Mike's age} - 4 = 24 - 4 = 20\n   \\]\n\n2. **Jeff's Age**: Jeff is 10 years older than Martha, so we can calculate Jeff's age as follows:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Jeff's age} = \\text{Martha's age} + 10 = 20 + 10 = 30\n   \\]\n\nTherefore, Jeff is 30 years old."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 81/100 path 3/5 answer="First, we determine Martha's age:\nMartha is 4 years younger than Mike, who is 24 years old.\nSo, Martha's age = 24 - 4 = 20 years old.\n\nNext, we calculate Jeff's age based on his relationship with Martha.\nJeff is 10 years older than Martha.\nSo, Jeff's age = 20 + 10 = 30 years old.\n\nTherefore, Jeff is 30 years old."
