[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 83/100 path 2/5 answer="To find out how many students are enrolled this year in the calligraphy class, we start with last year's enrollment (50) and calculate the increase by multiplying it by 20%.\n\nSo, \\( \\text{Enrollment this year} = \\text{Last year's enrollment} + (\\text{Increase}) \\)\n\\( \\text{Enrollment this year} = 50 + (0.20 \\times 50) \\)\n\nCalculating further:\n\n\\( \\text{Enrollment this year} = 50 + 10 \\)\n\\( \\text{Enrollment this year} = 60 \\)\n\nThus, there are 60 students currently enrolled in the calligraphy class this year."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 83/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 83/100 path 3/5 answer="To find the current number of students enrolled in the calligraphy class, we need to calculate a 20% increase from last year's enrollment of 50 students.\n\nFirst, let's calculate 20% of last year's enrollment:\n\\[ 20\\% \\text{ of } 50 = \\frac{20}{100} \\times 50 = 0.2 \\times 50 = 10 \\]\n\nNow, add this increase to last year's total:\n\\[ 50 + 10 = 60 \\]\n\nSo, there are 60 students currently enrolled in the calligraphy class this year."
