[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 89/100 path 3/5 answer='First, we calculate what 40% of his house value is:\n40% of $250,000 = 0.40 * $250,000 = $100,000\n\nNext, we calculate how much he used from his mortgage (40%) plus the amount he paid towards his debts (60%), and find out how much was left over:\n$100,000 (mortgage) + $100,000 (debts) - $100,000 (mortgage minus payments on debts) = $100,000\n\nSo, John had $100,000 leftover after paying back his loans.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 89/100 path 4/5 start
