[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 91/100 path 1/5 answer='To find out how many pomelos Eve gave away, we first calculate what fraction of the original amount she had when she was left with one-fourth of it. This can be calculated as 1/4 * 20 = 5 pomelos.\n\nEve ended up with these 5 pomelos but before giving them away, she was left with 1/4 of the total she started with. So, before giving away, she would have had (1/4) * 20 = 5 pomelos.\n\nTherefore, Eve gave away 5 - 5 = 0 pomelos.'
