[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 91/100 path 2/5 answer="To find out how many pomelos Eve gave away, we first calculate how many pomelos Eve gave away based on what she originally had, then subtract it from the original amount. Since Eve ended up with \\( \\frac{1}{4} \\) of what she initially had, the calculation would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Pomelos given away} = \\left( \\frac{1}{4} \\right) \\times 20 \\]\n\nLet's do the math:\n\\[ \\text{Pomelos given away} = \\frac{1}{4} \\times 20 = 5 \\]\n\nEve gave away 5 pomelos."
