[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 91/100 path 4/5 answer="To find out how many pomelos Eve gave away, let's break down the problem:\n\n1. Eve originally had 20 pieces of pomelos.\n2. After giving her friend some pomelos, she was left with \\( \\frac{1}{4} \\) of the original amount. Therefore, we calculate the remaining pomelos as follows:\n   \\[\n   \\text{Remaining pomelos} = 20 \\times \\frac{1}{4}\n   \\]\n   \nNow, let's perform the calculation:\n\\[\n20 \\times \\frac{1}{4} = 5\n\\]\n\nSo, Eve gave away **5** pieces of pomelos."
