[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 2/5 answer="First, let's calculate the daily consumption of dog food for both types of dogs:\n- A German Shepherd consumes 5 kg/day.\n- A Bulldog consumes 3 kg/day.\n\nNext, we'll determine how much dog food is needed per week:\n- For the German Shepherds: 3 dogs * 5 kg/day = 15 kg/week.\n- For the Bulldogs: 2 dogs * 3 kg/day = 6 kg/week.\n\nNow, adding these two amounts together gives us the total weekly consumption:\n\nWeekly consumption = (German Shepherds' consumption) + (Bulldogs' consumption)\n                    = 15 kg/week + 6 kg/week\n                    = 21 kg/week\n\nSo, the Kennel House will need 21 kilograms of dog food in a week."
