[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 4/5 answer='First, we calculate the total amount of dog food consumed daily:\n- Each German Shepherd eats 5 kg/day,\n- There are 3 German Shepherds,\n- Therefore, the total consumption for German Shepherds is 5 * 3 = 15 kg/day.\n\n- Each Bulldog eats 3 kg/day,\n- There are 2 Bulldogs,\n- Thus, the total consumption for Bulldogs is 3 * 2 = 6 kg/day.\n\nTo find out how much dog food they will need in a week (7 days), we multiply these amounts:\n15 kg/day * 7 days = 105 kg/day.\n\nTherefore, the total amount of dog food needed in a week is 105 kg/day * 7 days = 735 kg.'
