[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 1/5 answer="First, let's identify each sibling based on their ages:\n- One brother is 12 years old.\n- Two sisters are equally aged and are the same age as the older brother.\n- Therefore, the younger sister is also 12 years old.\n\nNow we know the following information about the siblings:\n- There are 2 brothers and 3 sisters (including the two younger sisters).\n- The younger sister is 12 years old.\n\nSo, the siblings consist of:\n- Brother 1 (age = 12)\n- Younger Sister (age = 12)\n- Older Brother (age = 12)\n\nNext, calculate the total age of all these siblings:\n- Total age = Brother's age + Younger Sister's age + Older Brother's age\n- Total age = 12 + 12 + 12 = 36\n\nTherefore, the total age of all these siblings is 36 years."
