[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 3/5 answer="First, let's identify the ages of the children:\n- Older brother (ages 16): This is half of the age of the younger brother (ages 12).\n- Two younger sisters (ages 16 each): These are the remaining siblings since they have all the same age.\n\nNow, we know the following:\n- Total age of the older brother: \\(16 \\times 2 = 32\\)\n- Total age of two younger sisters: \\(16 \\times 2 = 32\\)\n\nTo find the total age of all the siblings:\n- Elder brother's age = 16\n- Total age = Age of elder brother + Ages of the younger sisters\n- Total age = 16 + 32 + 32\n\nLet's calculate the total age now:\n\nTotal age = \\(16 + 32 + 32 = 80\\)\n\nSo, the total age of all these siblings is 80."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 4/5 answer="To find the total age of all these siblings, we first calculate the ages of the brothers and their sisters:\n\n- There are 3 sisters, each 16 years old.\n- One brother is 12 years old.\n- Therefore, the other brother is also 12 years old (half the age of the older brother).\n\nNow, let's sum up the ages of all the siblings:\n\n- Age of the younger sister = 16 years (sisters)\n- Age of the older brother = 12 years (given information)\n- Age of the two brothers = 12 + 12 = 24 years\n\nAdding these together gives us:\nTotal age of all siblings = 16 (sister) + 12 (older brother) + 24 (two brothers) = 52 years.\n\nSo, the total age of all these siblings is **52** years."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 5/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 5/5 answer='First, identify the ages of the brothers. Since one brother is 12 years old, he is half the age of the older brother, who is also 12 years old. This means the younger brother is also 12 years old.\n\nNext, we know there are 3 sisters, each 16 years old.\n\nNow, calculate the total age:\n- Older brother (12 years): \\(12 + 12 = 24\\)\n- Younger brother (12 years): \\(12\\)\n- Siblings (including the older brother and two sisters): \\(12 + 12 + 16 \\times 2 = 12 + 12 + 32 = 56\\)\n\nAdding up all the ages gives us: \n\\(24 + 12 + 32 + 56 = 124\\).\n\nSo, the total age of all these siblings is 124 years.'
