[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 2/5 answer='Firstly, we calculate how many cookies Randy had initially:\n- Oatmeal cookies: 9\n- Chocolate chip cookies: 4\n- Sugar cookies: 5\n\nThen, we subtract the ones he ate for snacks and gave to his friends:\n- Oatmeal cookies remaining: 9 - 2 (lunch) = 7\n- Chocolate chip cookies remaining: 4 (no change)\n- Sugar cookies remaining: 5 - 2 (gave away) = 3\n\nNext, we account for the cookies he baked:\n- Oatmeal cookies baked: 4\n- Chocolate chip cookies baked: 4\n- Sugar cookies baked: 4\n\nFinally, we sum up all the cookies:\n- Total cookies remaining: 7 (initial) + 4 (baked) + 4 (baked) + 4 (baked) = 19\n\nSo, Randy has 19 cookies now.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 3/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 3/5 answer='Randy starts with:\n- 9 oatmeal cookies\n- 4 chocolate chip cookies\n- 5 sugar cookies\n\nHe eats 3 cookies for lunch and gives away 2 sugar cookies, so he has:\n- 9 - 3 = 6 oatmeal cookies\n- 4 - 2 = 2 chocolate chip cookies\n- 5 - 2 = 3 sugar cookies left\n\nThen he bakes 4 of each flavor, so now he has:\n- 4 oatmeal cookies + 4 chocolate chip cookies + 4 sugar cookies = 12 cookies\n\nAdding all the flavors together, he ends up with:\n- 9 + 4 + 5 = 18 total cookies'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 4/5 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 4/5 answer='Firstly, we calculate how many cookies Randy had initially:\nOatmeal: 9 cookies\nChocolate Chip: 4 cookies\nSugar: 5 cookies\n\nAfter eating some, we subtract the eaten items:\nOatmeal: 9 - 3 = 6 cookies left\nChocolate Chip: 4 - 3 = 1 cookie left\nSugar: 5 - 2 = 3 cookies left\n\nThen, Randy bakes 4 of each flavor for dinner:\nFor Oatmeal: 4 oatmeal cookies (baked)\nFor Chocolate Chip: 4 chocolate chip cookies (baked)\nFor Sugar: 4 sugar cookies (baked)\n\nNow, we sum up all the remaining cookies:\nTotal Cookies = 6 (initial) + 4 (baked) + 4 (baked) + 4 (baked)\nTotal Cookies = 18 cookies\n\nSo, Randy has 18 cookies now.'
