[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 97/100 path 5/5 answer='First, we calculate how many cookies Randy has initially:\n- Oatmeal cookies: 9\n- Chocolate chip cookies: 4\n- Sugar cookies: 5\n\nTotal initial cookies: 9 + 4 + 5 = 18\n\nNext, we account for the cookies he ate:\n- 3 oatmeal cookies\n- 1 chocolate chip cookie (lunch)\n- 2 sugar cookies (dinner)\n\nNow we subtract these from the total initially:\n\nOatmeal cookies left: 9 - 3 = 6\nChocolate chip cookies left: 4 - 1 = 3\nSugar cookies left: 5 - 2 = 3\n\nAdding them up gives us the remaining number of cookies:\n\nTotal cookies left: 6 + 3 + 3 = 12\n\nRandy then bakes 4 of each flavor for dinner, so we multiply:\n\n4 oatmeal cookies\n4 chocolate chip cookies\n4 sugar cookies\n\nFinal count of cookies:\n- Oatmeal: 4 * 4 = 16\n- Chocolate chip: 4 * 4 = 16\n- Sugar: 4 * 4 = 16\n\nTotal remaining cookies:\n16 + 16 + 16 = 48\n\nThus, Randy still has 48 cookies now.'
