[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 98/100 path 2/5 answer="To find out how much money each person raised in total:\n\n1. Kim raised $320 more than Alexandra, so Kim's amount is $430 + $320.\n2. Maryam raised $400 more than Sarah, so Maryam's amount is $300 + $400.\n3. We can now calculate their individual amounts:\n   - Alexandra raised $430\n   - Kim raised $430 + $320 = $750\n   - Maryam raised $300 + $400 = $700\n\nNow we sum up all their amounts to get the total raised:\n\nTotal raised = Amount raised by Alexandra + Amount raised by Kim + Amount raised by Maryam\nTotal raised = $430 + $750 + $700\n\nTherefore, the total amount of money raised by all three girls is $1980."
