[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of kittens Patchy has:\nPatchy has had thrice the number of adopted kittens as Trixie, so Patchy has 3 * 12 = 36 kittens.\n\nNext, we add the number of kittens Patchy has to the number of kittens Trixie has:\nTotal kittens = 36 (Patchy) + 12 (Trixie) = 48 kittens.\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 48 kittens.'
