[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of kittens Patchy has: 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\nThen, we add the number of kittens Trixie has: 21 + 12 = 33 kittens.\nSo, the total number of kittens the Doubtfire family now has is 33 kittens.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 3/100 path 3/3 answer="First, we calculate the number of kittens Patchy has:\nPatchy has had thrice the number of kittens as the total number of kittens they initially had (which is 7). So, Patchy has had 3 * 7 = 21 kittens.\n\nNext, we add the number of kittens Trixie has had to the number of kittens Patchy has had:\nTrixie has had 12 kittens.\n\nNow, we sum up all the kittens:\nTotal kittens = Patchy's kittens + Trixie's kittens\nTotal kittens = 21 + 12\nTotal kittens = 33\n\nTherefore, the Doubtfire family now has 33 kittens."
