[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 6/100 path 1/3 answer="Let's denote the number of copies Harald sold as \\( H \\). According to the problem, Marilyn sold 10 times as many copies as Harald, so we can write:\n\\[ 10H = 88000 \\]\n\nTo find out how many copies Harald sold, we divide both sides of the equation by 10:\n\\[ H = \\frac{88000}{10} \\]\n\\[ H = 8800 \\]\n\nSo, Harald sold 8800 copies of his record."
