[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 start id=gsm8k_test_93
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 path 1/3 answer="Lee ran the 400-meter hurdles in 38 seconds. Since Lee could run it two seconds faster than Gerald, we first calculate how long it took Gerald to run the same distance:\n\n\\[ \\text{Time for Gerald} = \\text{Time for Lee} + 2 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Time for Gerald} = 38 + 2 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Time for Gerald} = 40 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\nGerald's improvement in time due to his diet was 10%, so we calculate his new running time:\n\n\\[ \\text{New Time for Gerald} = \\text{Original Time} \\times (1 + \\text{Improvement}) \\]\n\\[ \\text{New Time for Gerald} = 40 \\times (1 + 0.1) \\]\n\\[ \\text{New Time for Gerald} = 40 \\times 1.1 \\]\n\\[ \\text{New Time for Gerald} = 44 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\nTherefore, Gerald can run the 400-meter hurdles at a speed of 44 seconds per second."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 path 2/3 answer="First, we calculate Lee's original time to run the 400-meter hurdles:\nLee took 38 seconds.\n\nSince Lee was able to run the hurdles two seconds faster than Gerald, we subtract those two seconds from Lee's time to find out how long it takes Gerald to run them:\nGerald's time = Lee's time - 2 seconds\nGerald's time = 38 seconds - 2 seconds\nGerald's time = 36 seconds.\n\nNow, we know Gerald's initial running speed was 10% faster than Lee's. To find Lee's original speed, we divide Gerald's current speed by 1.1 (since he ran 10% faster):\nLee's original speed = Gerald's speed / 1.1\nLee's original speed = 36 seconds / 1.1\nLee's original speed = 32.73 seconds per second.\n\nTo find Gerald's current speed, we multiply his original speed by 1.1:\nGerald's current speed = Lee's original speed * 1.1\nGerald's current speed = 32.73 seconds per second * 1.1\nGerald's current speed = 36.003 seconds per second.\n\nTherefore, Gerald can run the 400-meter hurdles at a speed of 36.003 seconds per second."
