[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 start id=gsm8k_test_142
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 1/3 answer="To calculate how much money Jordan would earn in one week from playing video games, we first need to determine how many hours he spends on video games each day and then multiply that by the number of days in a week (assuming 7).\n\nJordan plays video games for 2 hours every day. So, in one week (7 days), he would play:\n\n2 hours/day × 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, let's calculate how much money he would earn from his part-time job at $10 per hour:\n\n14 hours/week × $10/hour = $140/week\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $140 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead."
