[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate how much Jordan earns from playing video games in one day:\n2 hours/day * $2/hour = $<<2*2=4>>4\n\nNext, we calculate how much Jordan earns from his part-time job:\n$10/hour * 5 hours/day = $<<10*5=50>>50\n\nNow, we find out how much Jordan earns in total in one week:\n$4/day * 7 days/week = $<<4*7=28>>28\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $28 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 10/100 done id=gsm8k_test_142 prediction="To calculate how much money Jordan would earn in one week from playing video games, we first need to determine how many hours he spends on video games each day and then multiply that by the number of days in a week (assuming 7).\n\nJordan plays video games for 2 hours every day. So, in one week (7 days), he would play:\n\n2 hours/day × 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, let's calculate how much money he would earn from his part-time job at $10 per hour:\n\n14 hours/week × $10/hour = $140/week\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $140 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead." gold='140' correct=False vote_counts={"To calculate how much money Jordan would earn in one week from playing video games, we first need to determine how many hours he spends on video games each day and then multiply that by the number of days in a week (assuming 7).\n\nJordan plays video games for 2 hours every day. So, in one week (7 days), he would play:\n\n2 hours/day × 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, let's calculate how much money he would earn from his part-time job at $10 per hour:\n\n14 hours/week × $10/hour = $140/week\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $140 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead.": 1, 'To calculate how much Jordan would earn in one week, we first need to determine how many hours he spends playing video games each day and multiply it by the number of days in a week (which is 7).\n\nJordan plays for 2 hours every day. So, in one week (7 days), he would play:\n\n2 hours/day × 7 days/week = 14 hours/week\n\nNow, we know that he earns $10 per hour at his part-time job. To find out how much he earns in one week, we multiply the total hours he plays by his hourly rate:\n\n$10/hour × 14 hours/week = $140/week\n\nSo, Jordan would earn $140 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead.': 1, 'First, we calculate how much Jordan earns from playing video games in one day:\n2 hours/day * $2/hour = $<<2*2=4>>4\n\nNext, we calculate how much Jordan earns from his part-time job:\n$10/hour * 5 hours/day = $<<10*5=50>>50\n\nNow, we find out how much Jordan earns in total in one week:\n$4/day * 7 days/week = $<<4*7=28>>28\n\nTherefore, Jordan would earn $28 in one week if he spent his video game time working instead.': 1}
