[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 11/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of Lego sets Johnny picked up:\n- One set with 500 pieces.\n- Another set with 3 times more pieces than the first, so \\(500 \\times 3 = 1500\\) pieces.\n- A third set with \\(1/4\\) the number of pieces as the second set, so \\(1500 / 4 = 375\\) pieces.\n\nAdding these together gives us the total number of Lego sets Johnny picked up: \\(500 + 1500 + 375 = 2375\\) pieces.\n\nSince each Lego set contains 500 pieces, the total number of Lego blocks Johnny picks up is \\(2375 \\times 500\\).\n\nTherefore, Johnny picks up \\(2375 \\times 500 = 1187500\\) Lego blocks.'
