[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 start id=gsm8k_test_161
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 1/3 answer='Anakin caught 10 + 6 + 3 = 19 fish.\nLocsin caught 10 - 5 = 5 starfish.\nLocsin caught 6 - 3 = 3 sea horses.\nLocsin caught 3 + 2 = 5 clownfish.\nSo, together they caught 19 + 5 + 3 + 5 = 28 fish.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many fish each person caught:\n\nAnakin:\nStarfish: 10\nSea horses: 6\nClownfish: 3\n\nLocsin:\nStarfish: 10 - 5 = 5\nSea horses: 6 - 3 = 3\nClownfish: 3 + 2 = 5\n\nNow we can sum up all the fish they caught:\n\nTotal fish = Starfish + Sea horses + Clownfish\nTotal fish = 10 + 6 + 3 + 5 + 5\nTotal fish = 29\n\nSo, Anakin and Locsin were able to catch 29 fish in total."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 12/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many fish Anakin and Locsin caught, we'll first calculate the number each of them caught individually based on their respective catches:\n\nAnakin:\n- Starfish: 10\n- Sea horses: 6\n- Clownfish: 3\n\nLocsin:\n- Starfish: 10 - 5 = 5\n- Sea horses: 6 - 3 = 3\n- Clownfish: 3 + 2 = 5\n\nNow, let's sum up all the fish they caught together:\n\nTotal fish caught = (Anakin's starfish + Anakin's sea horses + Anakin's clownfish) + (Locsin's starfish + Locsin's sea horses + Locsin's clownfish)\nTotal fish caught = (10 + 6 + 3) + (5 + 3 + 5)\nTotal fish caught = 19 + 13\nTotal fish caught = 32\n\nSo, Anakin and Locsin were able to catch a total of 32 fish."
