[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 start id=gsm8k_test_163
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how much all the toys are worth, we first calculate the total cost of each type of toy:\n\n1. Dolls: Since the doll costs as much as 3 action figures, and each action figure costs $5, the dolls will also cost $15 (since $15 ÷ 3 = $5).\n2. Red cars: Each red car costs $4, so 5 red cars would cost $20 (since $4 × 5 = $20).\n\nNow, let's sum up the total cost of all the toys:\nTotal cost = Cost of dolls + Cost of red cars + Cost of action figures\nTotal cost = $15 + $20 + $5\nTotal cost = $40\n\nTherefore, all the toys together are worth $40."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how much each type of toy costs:\n\n- Red cars: Since they cost as much as 3 action figures, we can assume that each red car costs 3 * $5 = $<<3*5=15>>15.\n- Dolls: We know that dolls cost as much as 3 action figures, so each doll costs $15.\n- Action figures: Each action figure costs $5.\n\nNow, let's find out the total cost of the toys:\n\n- Total cost of red cars: 5 * $15 = $<<5*15=75>>75.\n- Total cost of dolls: 1 * $15 = $<<1*15=15>>15.\n- Total cost of action figures: 3 * $5 = $<<3*5=15>>15.\n\nAdding these together gives us the total cost of all the toys:\n\n$75 + $15 + $15 = $<<75+15+15=105>>105.\n\nSo, all the toys together are worth $105."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 13/100 path 3/3 answer="First, let's determine how much each type of toy costs:\n\n- Doll: Costs as much as 3 action figures, so it would cost $15 (since 3 action figures cost $5).\n- Red car: Costs $4.\n- Action figures: Each costs $5, so 3 action figures would cost $15.\n\nNow we can calculate the total cost of all the toys:\n- Doll: $15\n- Red car: $4\n- Action figures: $15\n\nTotal cost = $15 + $4 + $15 = $34\n\nTherefore, all the toys together are worth $34."
