[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 14/100 path 3/3 answer="To find the total number of crabs Rani, Monic, and Bo have together, we first determine how many crabs each person has:\n\n1. Bo has 40 crabs.\n2. Monic has 4 fewer crabs than Bo, so Monic has \\(40 - 4 = 36\\) crabs.\n3. Rani has 10 more crabs than Monic, so Rani has \\(36 + 10 = 46\\) crabs.\n\nNow, we sum up the crabs of all three:\n\n\\(Bo\\)'s crabs: 40\nMonic's crabs: 36\nRani's crabs: 46\n\nTotal crabs = \\(40 + 36 + 46 = 122\\).\n\nTherefore, the total number of crabs the three have together is 122."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 14/100 done id=gsm8k_test_178 prediction='122' gold='122' correct=True vote_counts={'122': 2, "To find the total number of crabs Rani, Monic, and Bo have together, we first determine how many crabs each person has:\n\n1. Bo has 40 crabs.\n2. Monic has 4 fewer crabs than Bo, so Monic has \\(40 - 4 = 36\\) crabs.\n3. Rani has 10 more crabs than Monic, so Rani has \\(36 + 10 = 46\\) crabs.\n\nNow, we sum up the crabs of all three:\n\n\\(Bo\\)'s crabs: 40\nMonic's crabs: 36\nRani's crabs: 46\n\nTotal crabs = \\(40 + 36 + 46 = 122\\).\n\nTherefore, the total number of crabs the three have together is 122.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 start id=gsm8k_test_189
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate the total amount spent on tickets:\n$20.25 (for tickets) + $4.50 (less on food) = $24.75\n\nNext, we know they spent $33 on each ride:\n2 rides * $33 per ride = $66\n\nNow, let's add up all their expenses:\nTickets: $24.75\nFood: $66\nRides: $66\n\nTotal cost: $24.75 + $66 + $66 = $156.75\n\nFinally, we'll divide the total cost by the number of people to find out how much each person paid:\n$156.75 / 3 people = $52.25 per person\n\nSo, each friend pays $52.25."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 2/3 answer="First, we calculate the total cost of the tickets:\nTickets cost: $20.25\n\nNext, we find out how much they spent on food:\nFood cost: $20.25 - $4.50 = $15.75\n\nThen, we calculate the cost of the rides:\nRides cost: $33 \\times 2 = $66\n\nNow, let's sum up all the expenses:\nTotal expense: Tickets + Food + Rides\nTotal expense: $20.25 + $15.75 + $66\nTotal expense: $102\n\nFinally, we divide the total expense by the number of people (which is 3) to find out how much each person paid:\nEach person's share: Total expense / Number of people\nEach person's share: $102 / 3\nEach person's share: $34\n\nSo, each friend pays $34."
