[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 3/3 answer="First, let's calculate the total amount spent on the tickets:\nTickets cost: $20.25\n\nNow, we know they spent $4.50 less on food than on the tickets:\nFood cost: $20.25 - $4.50 = $15.75\n\nThey also went on 2 different rides which cost $33 each:\nRides cost: $33 x 2 = $66\n\nNow, let's sum up all the expenses:\nTotal expenses: Tickets + Food + Rides\nTotal expenses: $20.25 + $15.75 + $66\nTotal expenses: $102\n\nFinally, we'll divide the total expenses by the number of people (3) to find out how much each person paid:\nAmount each person pays: $102 / 3\nAmount each person pays: $34\n\nSo, each of them paid $34."
