[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 start id=gsm8k_test_191
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 1/3 answer='To find out how many pounds of insects the entire flock needs per day, we first calculate the weekly consumption:\n\nWeekly consumption = Number of ducks × Pounds of insects per duck per week\n                           = 10 × 3.5 pounds\n                           = 35 pounds\n\nNow, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly consumption by 7 to get the daily requirement:\n\nDaily consumption = Weekly consumption ÷ Days in a week\n                       = 35 pounds ÷ 7 days\n                       = 5 pounds/day\n\nTherefore, the entire flock needs 5 pounds of insects per day.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 2/3 answer='To find out how many pounds of insects the entire flock needs per day, we first calculate the weekly consumption for all the ducks together:\n\nEach duck eats 3.5 pounds per week.\n\nSo, for 10 ducks:\n\\[ 10 \\text{ ducks} \\times 3.5 \\text{ pounds/duck} = 35 \\text{ pounds/week} \\]\n\nNow, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly consumption by 7 to get the daily requirement:\n\n\\[ \\frac{35 \\text{ pounds/week}}{7 \\text{ days/week}} = 5 \\text{ pounds/day} \\]\n\nTherefore, the entire flock needs 5 pounds of insects per day.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 16/100 path 3/3 answer='To find out how many pounds of insects the entire flock of ten ducks needs per day, we first calculate the weekly requirement:\n\nWeekly requirement = 3.5 pounds/duck × 10 ducks/flock = 35 pounds/flock\n\nNow, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly requirement by 7 to get the daily requirement:\n\nDaily requirement = 35 pounds/flock ÷ 7 days/week = 5 pounds/day\n\nTherefore, the flocks of ten ducks need 5 pounds of insects per day.'
