 weekly requirement:\n\nWeekly requirement = 3.5 pounds/duck × 10 ducks/flock = 35 pounds/flock\n\nNow, since there are 7 days in a week, we divide the weekly requirement by 7 to get the daily requirement:\n\nDaily requirement = 35 pounds/flock ÷ 7 days/week = 5 pounds/day\n\nTherefore, the flocks of ten ducks need 5 pounds of insects per day.': 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 start id=gsm8k_test_198
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of cards collected each month:\n- In the first month, she collected \\(3 \\times 20 = 60\\) cards.\n- In the second month, she collected \\(60 - 20 = 40\\) cards.\n- In the third month, she collected \\(2 \\times (20 + 60) = 2 \\times 80 = 160\\) cards.\n\nNow, we sum up all the cards collected over the three months:\n\\[20 + 60 + 40 + 160 = 280\\]\n\nSo, the total number of cards Elaine has now is \\(280\\).'
