[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 17/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate how many cards Elaine collected each month:\n- In the first month, she collected \\(3 \\times 20 = 60\\) cards.\n- In the second month, she collected \\(60 - 20 = 40\\) cards.\n- In the third month, she collected \\(2 \\times (20 + 60) = 2 \\times 80 = 160\\) cards.\n\nNow, we sum up all the cards collected over the three months:\n\\[20 + 60 + 40 + 160 = 280\\]\n\nFinally, we add these cards to the initial amount of cards Elaine had:\n\\[20 + 280 = 300\\]\n\nSo, Elaine has 300 Pokemon cards now in total.'
