[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 start id=gsm8k_test_228
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate how many pieces Kalinda can add per minute:\nKalinda adds 4 pieces per minute.\n\nHer mom can add half as many pieces per minute as Kalinda, so:\nMom adds 4 / 2 = 2 pieces per minute.\n\nTogether, they can add:\n4 + 2 = <<4+2=6>>6 pieces per minute.\n\nTo find out how long it takes to complete the puzzle, we divide the total number of pieces by their combined rate:\n360 pieces / 6 pieces per minute = <<360/6=60>>60 minutes.\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, the time it takes to complete the puzzle is:\n60 minutes / 60 minutes per hour = <<60/60=1>>1 hour.\n\nTherefore, it will take them 1 hour to complete the puzzle.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 20/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate how many pieces Kalinda can add per minute:\nKalinda adds 4 pieces per minute.\n\nHer mom adds half as many pieces per minute as Kalinda, so:\nMom adds \\( \\frac{4}{2} = 2 \\) pieces per minute.\n\nTogether, they can add \\( 4 + 2 = 6 \\) pieces per minute.\n\nTo find out how long it takes to complete the puzzle, we divide the total number of pieces by their combined rate:\n\\( \\text{Time (minutes)} = \\frac{360}{6} = 60 \\) minutes.\n\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, we convert the time into hours:\n\\( \\text{Time (hours)} = \\frac{60}{60} = 1 \\) hour.\n\nTherefore, it will take them 1 hour to complete the puzzle.'
