 many nongendered children as boys, so:\n\\[ \\text{Number of nongendered children} = \\frac{1}{10} \\times \\text{Number of boys} = \\frac{1}{10} \\times 30 = 3 \\]\n\nNow, we can find the total number of children by adding the number of boys, girls, and nongendered children together:\n\\[ \\text{Total number of children} = \\text{Number of boys} + \\text{Number of girls} + \\text{Number of nongendered children} = 30 + 90 + 3 = 123 \\]\n\nTherefore, the total number of children in the classroom is 123.": 1, 'First, we find out how many girls there are:\nNumber of girls = Number of boys × 3 = 30 × 3 = 90\n\nNext, we calculate the number of nongendered children:\nNumber of nongendered children = Number of boys ÷ 10 = 30 ÷ 10 = 3\n\nNow, we can find the total number of children:\nTotal children = Number of boys + Number of girls + Number of nongendered children = 30 + 90 + 3 = 123\n\nSo, the total number of children in the classroom is 123.': 1}
