[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 start id=gsm8k_test_334
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how many guns each person would have if they shared them equally, we first need to sum up all the guns:\n\nDJ's guns: 8\nNick's guns: 10\nRJ's guns: 1\nRichard's guns: 5\n\nTotal number of guns = 8 + 10 + 1 + 5 = 24 guns\n\nIf they were to share these equally among themselves, we divide the total number of guns by the number of people (which is 5):\n\n24 ÷ 5 = 4.8\n\nSince you can't have a fraction of a gun, it means that each person would get 4 full guns, and there would be 4.8 extra guns left over. So, each person would have 4 full guns plus 0.8 extra guns.\n\nTherefore, each person would end up with 4 full guns and 0.8 extra guns."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 2/3 answer="To find out how many guns each person would have if they shared them equally, we first need to calculate the total number of guns:\n\nDJ: 8 guns\nNick: 10 guns\nRJ: 1 gun\nRichard: 5 guns\n\nTotal number of guns = 8 + 10 + 1 + 5 = 24 guns\n\nIf they were to share these equally among all five people, we divide the total number of guns by the number of people:\n\n24 guns ÷ 5 people = 4.8 guns/person\n\nSince you can't have a fraction of a gun, we'll round down to the nearest whole number. Each person would get 4 guns, and there would be 4 guns left over (since 24 divided by 5 is 4 with a remainder of 4)."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 27/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many guns each person would have if they shared them equally, we first need to determine the total number of guns:\n\nTotal guns = DJ's guns + Nick's guns + RJ's guns + Richard's guns\nTotal guns = 8 + 10 + 1 + 5\nTotal guns = 24\n\nNow, since there are four people (Nick, Richard, Jason, and DJ), we divide the total number of guns by the number of people:\n\nGuns per person = Total guns ÷ Number of people\nGuns per person = 24 ÷ 4\nGuns per person = 6\n\nSo, if they were to share their guns equally, each person would have 6 guns."
