[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 28/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate each activity's duration:\n\n1. Yoga class: 1 hour\n2. Cooking class: 3 times as long as the yoga class, so 1 hour * 3 = 3 hours\n3. Cheese-tasting event: Half an hour (0.5 hours)\n4. Museum tour: Half as long as the cooking class, so 3 hours / 2 = 1.5 hours\n5. Errands: 2 hours\n\nNow, let's sum up all the durations:\n1 + 3 + 0.5 + 1.5 + 2 = 8 hours\n\nTherefore, all of Peyton's after-work activities will take 8 hours total."
