[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 30/100 path 1/3 answer="First, we calculate how many steps Elliott took to go to and from school:\n- Steps to school: \\( \\frac{10,000}{2} = 5,000 \\) steps.\n- Steps from school: \\( 5,000 \\times 2 = 10,000 \\) steps (since it's one-way).\n\nNext, we account for the additional steps taken walking with his friend:\n- Additional steps: 1,000 steps.\n\nNow, let's sum up all the steps:\n- Total steps before jogging: \\( 5,000 + 10,000 + 1,000 = 16,000 \\) steps.\n\nAfter jogging, he had 2,000 steps left:\n- Steps remaining: \\( 16,000 - 2,000 = 14,000 \\) steps.\n\nTherefore, Elliott took 14,000 steps during his jog."
