[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 31/100 path 1/3 answer="First, we calculate half of Indras' name length: 6 / 2 = 3.\nThen, we add 4 to get the number of letters in Indras' sister's name: 3 + 4 = <<3+4=7>>7.\nFinally, we add the lengths of both names together: 6 + 7 = <<6+7=13>>13.\nTherefore, Indras and her sister's combined names have 13 letters."
