[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate how many dragons each person slew:\n\nPrince Thaddeus: 100 dragons\nPrince Arthur: 3/4 * 100 dragons = 75 dragons\nPrince Walter: 2 * 75 dragons = 150 dragons\nPrince Bruce: 1/5 * 150 dragons = 30 dragons\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slayed 30 dragons.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate how many dragons each person killed:\n\nPrince Thaddeus: 100 dragons\nPrince Arthur: Three-quarters as many as Prince Thaddeus = (3/4) * 100 = 75 dragons\nPrince Walter: Twice as many as Prince Arthur = 2 * 75 = 150 dragons\nPrince Bruce: One-fifth as many as Prince Walter = (1/5) * 150 = 30 dragons\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slain 30 dragons.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 32/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate how many dragons Prince Arthur killed:\nPrince Arthur killed 100 dragons (as stated).\n\nNext, we determine how many dragons Prince Walter killed:\nPrince Walter killed three-quarters as many dragons as Prince Arthur, so:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Walter} = \\frac{3}{4} \\times 100 = 75 \\]\n\nThen, we figure out how many dragons Prince Bruce killed:\nPrince Bruce killed two-thirds as many dragons as Prince Walter, so:\n\\[ \\text{Dragons killed by Bruce} = \\frac{2}{3} \\times 75 = 50 \\]\n\nTherefore, Prince Bruce has slain 50 dragons.'
