[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 36/100 start id=gsm8k_test_449
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 36/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 36/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how many crayons Beatrice bought in total, we'll first calculate the number of crayons from the six packets with eight pieces and then the number from the four packets with sixteen pieces.\n\nFor the six packets with eight pieces:\n\\( 6 \\text{ packets} \\times 8 \\text{ pieces/packet} = 48 \\text{ pieces} \\)\n\nFor the four packets with sixteen pieces:\n\\( 4 \\text{ packets} \\times 16 \\text{ pieces/packet} = 64 \\text{ pieces} \\)\n\nNow, we add these two amounts together to get the total number of crayons:\n\\( 48 + 64 = 112 \\text{ pieces} \\)\n\nTherefore, Beatrice bought a total of 112 crayons."
