[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 36/100 path 2/3 answer='To find out how many crayons Beatrice bought in total, we first calculate the number of crayons from the six packets with eight pieces each:\n\n\\( 6 \\text{ packets} \\times 8 \\text{ pieces/packet} = 48 \\text{ crayons} \\)\n\nNext, we calculate the number of crayons from the four packets with sixteen pieces each:\n\n\\( 4 \\text{ packets} \\times 16 \\text{ pieces/packet} = 64 \\text{ crayons} \\)\n\nNow, we add these two amounts together to get the total number of crayons Beatrice bought:\n\n\\( 48 \\text{ crayons} + 64 \\text{ crayons} = 112 \\text{ crayons} \\)\n\nTherefore, Beatrice bought a total of 112 crayons.'
