[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 start id=gsm8k_test_548
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 1/3 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can subtract the total weight loss over the 3 months from his final weight. \n\nHe lost 10 pounds each month for 3 months, so the total weight loss is:\n10 pounds/month * 3 months = 30 pounds\n\nHis final weight was 70 pounds, so his initial weight would have been:\n70 pounds (final weight) - 30 pounds (weight loss) = 40 pounds\n\nTherefore, Mark's initial weight was 40 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 2/3 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can start with the information given about his weight loss over time. We know that he lost 10 pounds per month for 3 months. So, his total weight loss would be:\n\n\\( \\text{Total Weight Loss} = \\text{Weight Loss Per Month} \\times \\text{Number of Months} \\)\n\n\\( \\text{Total Weight Loss} = 10 \\, \\text{pounds/month} \\times 3 \\, \\text{months} \\)\n\n\\( \\text{Total Weight Loss} = 30 \\, \\text{pounds} \\)\n\nSince his final weight was 70 pounds, we can subtract his total weight loss from his final weight to find out how much he weighed before losing those pounds:\n\n\\( \\text{Initial Weight} = \\text{Final Weight} + \\text{Total Weight Loss} \\)\n\n\\( \\text{Initial Weight} = 70 \\, \\text{pounds} + 30 \\, \\text{pounds} \\)\n\n\\( \\text{Initial Weight} = 100 \\, \\text{pounds} \\)\n\nTherefore, Mark's initial weight was 100 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 48/100 path 3/3 answer="To find Mark's initial weight, we can set up an equation based on the information given:\n\nLet \\( W \\) represent Mark's initial weight in pounds.\n\nSince Mark lost 10 pounds per month for 3 months, his total weight loss is:\n\\[ 10 \\text{ pounds/month} \\times 3 \\text{ months} = 30 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nMark's final weight is given as 70 pounds. Therefore, we can write the equation:\n\\[ W - 30 \\text{ pounds} = 70 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSolving for \\( W \\):\n\\[ W = 70 + 30 \\]\n\\[ W = 100 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo, Mark's initial weight was 100 pounds."
