ial weight in pounds.\n\nSince Mark lost 10 pounds per month for 3 months, his total weight loss is:\n\\[ 10 \\text{ pounds/month} \\times 3 \\text{ months} = 30 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nMark's final weight is given as 70 pounds. Therefore, we can write the equation:\n\\[ W - 30 \\text{ pounds} = 70 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSolving for \\( W \\):\n\\[ W = 70 + 30 \\]\n\\[ W = 100 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo, Mark's initial weight was 100 pounds.": 1}
