[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 49/100 path 3/3 answer="To calculate Antonella's earnings, we first determine how much commission she received from selling $2500 worth of goods:\n\n$2500 (total sales) * 30% (commission rate) = $750\n\nNext, we account for the additional 10% commission for sales above $1000:\n\n$2500 (total sales) + ($2500 - $1000) * 10% = $2500 + $1500 = $4000\n\nNow, we add the base commission to the additional commission to find the total earnings:\n\n$750 (base commission) + $4000 (additional commission) = $4750\n\nTherefore, Antonella earned $4750."
