[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 1/3 answer='To determine how much more expensive the boots are on eBay compared to Amazon, we first calculate the total cost of the boots at each store:\n\nAt Amazon:\nCost of boots + Shipping = $16 + $4 = $20\n\nAt eBay:\nCost of boots + Shipping (twice the cost on Amazon) = $13 + $2 * $4 = $13 + $8 = $21\n\nNow, we find the difference between the cost at eBay and Amazon:\n$21 - $20 = $1\n\nTherefore, the boots are $1 more expensive on eBay than they are on Amazon.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the total cost of the boots on both Amazon and eBay:\n\nOn Amazon:\nCost of boots + Shipping = $16 + $4 = $20\n\nOn eBay:\nCost of boots + Shipping = $13 + (2 * $4) = $13 + $8 = $21\n\nNow, we find the difference between the cost on eBay and the cost on Amazon:\n$21 - $20 = $1\n\nSo, the boots are $1 more expensive on eBay than they are on Amazon.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 52/100 path 3/3 answer='To find out how much more expensive the boots are on eBay compared to Amazon, we first calculate the total cost of the boots at both places:\n\nOn Amazon:\nCost of boots + Shipping = $16 + $4 = $20\n\nOn eBay:\nCost of boots + Shipping (twice the cost on Amazon) = $13 + ($13 * 2) = $13 + $26 = $39\n\nNow, we subtract the cost on Amazon from the cost on eBay to find the difference:\n\nDifference = Cost on eBay - Cost on Amazon = $39 - $20 = $19\n\nSo, the boots are $19 more expensive on eBay than they are on Amazon.'
