[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 55/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how many miles Alisa and Stanley biked in total, we first calculate the distance each person biked separately:\n\nAlisa's distance:\nDistance = Speed × Time\nDistance = 12 mph × 4.5 h\nDistance = 54 miles\n\nStanley's distance:\nDistance = Speed × Time\nDistance = 10 mph × 2.5 h\nDistance = 25 miles\n\nNow, we add their distances together to get the total distance they biked:\n\nTotal distance = Alisa's distance + Stanley's distance\nTotal distance = 54 miles + 25 miles\nTotal distance = 79 miles\n\nSo, Alisa and Stanley biked a total of 79 miles."
