[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 57/100 path 1/3 answer="To find out how much 10 lollipops and 10 candies will cost, we first calculate the total cost of the lollipops and candies Manolo already bought.\n\nManolo bought:\n- 5 lollipops at $0.40 each\n- 4 candies at $3.20 each\n\nTotal cost for lollipops = 5 × $0.40 = $<<5×0.40=2>>2\nTotal cost for candies = 4 × $3.20 = $<<4×3.20=12.80>>12.80\n\nNow, let's add these amounts together:\n\nTotal cost for lollipops + Total cost for candies = $2 + $12.80 = $<<2+12.80=14.80>>14.80\n\nIf we want to know the cost for 10 lollipops and 10 candies, we simply multiply the total cost for one set by 10:\n\nCost for 10 lollipops + Cost for 10 candies = $14.80 × 10 = $<<14.80×10=148>>148\n\nTherefore, 10 lollipops and 10 candies will cost Manolo $148."
