[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 start id=gsm8k_test_696
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 1/3 answer="First, we calculate how many points each student has:\n- Adam: 50 points\n- Betty: 30% more than Adam, so \\(50 + (50 \\times 0.3) = 50 + 15 = 65\\) points\n- Marta: 3 times more than Tom, so \\(30 \\times 3 = 90\\) points\n- Tom: 30 points less than Betty, so \\(65 - 30 = 35\\) points\n\nNow let's sum up the points of all students:\n\\[50 + 65 + 90 + 35 = 240\\]\n\nSince the minimum threshold for the trip is 400 points, the class needs:\n\\[400 - 240 = 160\\] points to reach the minimum threshold.\n\nTherefore, the class is missing \\(160 - 240 = -80\\) points, but since it's negative, it indicates that the class already has more points than needed to meet the minimum threshold. Thus, the class is **short** by 80 points."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 2/3 answer='that the class is already above the minimum threshold so no points are needed'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many points the class needs to reach the minimum threshold of 400 points to go on the trip, we'll first calculate the points each student has based on the given information:\n\n1. Adam has 50 points.\n2. Betty collected 30% more than Adam, so she collected \\(50 + (50 \\times 0.3) = 50 + 15 = 65\\) points.\n3. Marta collected 3 times more than Tom, so she collected \\(30 \\times 30 = 900\\) points.\n4. Tom has 30 points less than Betty, so he has \\(65 - 30 = 35\\) points.\n\nNow let's sum up all the points:\n\\[Adam\\)'s\\ points + Betty\\)'s\\ points + Marta\\)'s\\ points + Tom's\\ points = \\(50 + 65 + 900 + 35 = 1090\\)\n\nSince the minimum threshold is 400 points, the class needs \\(400 - 1090 = -690\\), but since it's negative, it means they have already exceeded the threshold by 690 points.\n\nTherefore, the class is over the threshold by 690 points."
