[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 59/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's find out how much money each person received based on the given ratio of 3:2. Since they divided $100 in the ratio, we can set up the equation:\n\n\\[ \\frac{3}{5} \\times 100 = 60 \\]\n\nSo, each part of the ratio is worth $60. Now, if Gerald spent $10 on a book, his remaining amount would be:\n\n\\[ 60 - 10 = 50 \\]\n\nTherefore, Gerald had $50 left."
