[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 start id=gsm8k_test_758
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 1/3 answer='To calculate the price after applying the 5% discount:\n\n1. First, find the amount of the discount:\n   Discount = Marked Price × Percentage Discount\n            = $140 × 0.05\n            = $7\n\n2. Then, subtract the discount from the marked price:\n   Final Price = Marked Price - Discount\n              = $140 - $7\n              = $133\n\nSo, you will pay $133 after the discount.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 2/3 answer='To calculate the discounted price, we first find the amount of the discount using the formula:\n\nDiscount = (Percentage Discount / 100) × Original Price\n\nFor this problem:\nPercentage Discount = 5%\nOriginal Price = $140\n\nDiscount = (5/100) × $140 = $7\n\nNow, subtract the discount from the original price to get the final price:\n\nFinal Price = Original Price - Discount\nFinal Price = $140 - $7 = $133\n\nSo, you will pay $133 after the discount.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 64/100 path 3/3 answer='To calculate the discounted price, we first find the amount of the discount:\n\nDiscount = Marked Price × Discount Percentage\n\nMarked Price = $140\nDiscount Percentage = 5%\n\nDiscount = $140 × 5% = $140 × 0.05 = $7\n\nNow, subtract the discount from the marked price to get the final price:\n\nFinal Price = Marked Price - Discount\nFinal Price = $140 - $7 = $133\n\nSo, you will pay $133 after the discount.'
