[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 start id=gsm8k_test_778
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 1/3 answer='To calculate the total cost, we first need to determine the weight of each type of fruit Winston picked:\n\n- Peaches: 6 pounds\n- Plums: 8 pounds\n- Apricots: 6 pounds\n\nNext, we multiply the weight by the price per unit (which is the same for all fruits):\n\n- Cost of peaches: 6 pounds × $2.00/pound = $12.00\n- Cost of plums: 8 pounds × $1.00/pound = $8.00\n- Cost of apricots: 6 pounds × $3.00/pound = $18.00\n\nNow, we add these amounts together to find the total cost:\n\n$12.00 + $8.00 + $18.00 = $38.00\n\nTherefore, Winston spent $38.00 on fruit at the local Pick Your Own fruit orchard.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 2/3 answer='To find out how much Winston spent on his fruit, we first calculate the cost of each type of fruit he picked:\n\n- Peaches: He picked 6 pounds at $2.00 per pound, so the cost is 6 * $2.00 = $<<6*2=12>>12.\n- Plums: He picked 8 pounds at $1.00 per pound, so the cost is 8 * $1.00 = $<<8*1=8>>8.\n- Apricots: He picked 6 pounds at $3.00 per pound, so the cost is 6 * $3.00 = $<<6*3=18>>18.\n\nNow, we add up all the costs:\n$12 (peaches) + $8 (plums) + $18 (apricots) = $<<12+8+18=38>>38.\n\nSo, Winston spent $38 on his fruit.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 67/100 path 3/3 answer="To calculate the total cost, we first need to find out how many pounds of each type of fruit Winston bought:\n\nPeaches: 6 pounds\nPlums: 8 pounds\nApricots: 6 pounds\n\nNow, let's calculate the cost for each type of fruit:\n\nCost of peaches: 6 pounds * $2.00/pound = $12.00\nCost of plums: 8 pounds * $1.00/pound = $8.00\nCost of apricots: 6 pounds * $3.00/pound = $18.00\n\nFinally, we'll add up all the costs to get the total amount spent:\n\nTotal cost = Cost of peaches + Cost of plums + Cost of apricots\nTotal cost = $12.00 + $8.00 + $18.00\nTotal cost = $38.00\n\nTherefore, Winston spent $38.00 on fruit."
