[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 70/100 path 2/3 answer="To find out how much money Julieta and Rafaela received as tips together, we first need to calculate how much Rafaela received. Since each of the 40 customers gave her $20 in tips, Rafaela received:\n\n40 customers * $20/customer = $<<40*20=800>>800\n\nJulieta received 10% less money than Rafaela, so we'll subtract 10% from Rafaela's amount to find out how much Julieta got:\n\n$800 - (10% of $800) = $800 - ($800 * 0.1) = $800 - $80 = $<<800-80=720>>720\n\nNow, to find out how much they both received altogether, we add their individual amounts together:\n\nRafaela's total + Julieta's total = $800 + $720 = $<<800+720=1520>>1520\n\nTherefore, Julieta and Rafaela received a combined total of $1520 as tips."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 70/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 70/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how much money Julieta and Rafaela received as tips together, we first need to calculate how much Rafaela received from the tips. Since each customer who came gave Rafaela $20 in tips, and there were 40 customers, Rafaela received:\n\n\\[ \\text{Rafaela's total} = 40 \\times 20 = \\$<<40*20=800>>800 \\]\n\nJulieta received 10% less money than Rafaela. To find out how much that is, we calculate 90% (since 10% is 0.1) of Rafaela's total:\n\n\\[ \\text{Julieta's total} = 800 \\times (1 - 0.10) = 800 \\times 0.90 = \\$<<800*0.90=720>>720 \\]\n\nNow, to find the total amount of money both Julieta and Rafaela received as tips together, we add their individual totals:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total} = \\text{Julieta's total} + \\text{Rafaela's total} = 720 + 800 = \\$<<720+800=1520>>1520 \\]\n\nSo, Julieta and Rafaela received a total of $1520 as tips."
