[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 start id=gsm8k_test_864
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 1/3 answer='First, we calculate the total number of burritos given out to the students:\n\nTotal burritos given out = Number of students × Burritos per student\nTotal burritos given out = 50 × 10 = 500\n\nNext, we subtract the number of burritos eaten by Mr. George from the total number of burritos given out:\n\nLeftover burritos = Total burritos given out - Burritos eaten by Mr. George\nLeftover burritos = 500 - 20 = 480\n\nTherefore, the total number of leftover burritos from the picnic is 480.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 2/3 answer='To find out how many leftover burritos George had, we first need to determine the total number of burritos distributed among the students. Each of the 50 students received 10 burritos, so:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total burritos distributed} = 50 \\times 10 = 500 \\]\n\nGeorge ate 20 of these burritos, so the number of remaining burritos is:\n\n\\[ \\text{Remaining burritos} = 500 - 20 = 480 \\]\n\nTherefore, the total number of leftover burritos from the picnic is 480.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we calculate the total number of burritos given out to all students:\n\\[ \\text{Total burritos} = 50 \\times 10 = 500 \\]\n\nNext, we subtract the number of burritos eaten by Mr. George:\n\\[ \\text{Burritos eaten by Mr. George} = 20 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Leftover burritos} = 500 - 20 = 480 \\]\n\nSo, the total number of leftover burritos is **480**.'
