[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 start id=gsm8k_test_865
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 1/3 answer='To find out how many yellow cars there are, we can work backwards from the information given:\n\n1. We know there are 12 red cars.\n2. There are 2 fewer green cars than red cars, so there are 12 - 2 = 10 green cars.\n3. Green cars are three times the number of blue cars, so there are 10 / 3 ≈ 3.33 (rounded down to 3) blue cars.\n4. Blue cars are yellow cars, so there are 3 yellow cars.\n\nTherefore, the number of yellow cars is 3.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the number of green cars:\nGreen cars = Red cars - 2 = 12 - 2 = 10\n\nNext, we calculate the number of blue cars:\nBlue cars = Green cars * 3 = 10 * 3 = 30\n\nNow, we know the total number of cars is 75, so we can subtract the known numbers of red, green, and blue cars from the total to find out how many yellow cars there are:\nYellow cars = Total cars - (Red cars + Green cars + Blue cars)\nYellow cars = 75 - (12 + 10 + 30) = 75 - 52 = 23\n\nSo, the rink has 23 yellow cars.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 72/100 path 3/3 answer='First, we find out how many green cars there are:\nGreen cars = Red cars - 2 = 12 - 2 = 10\n\nNext, we calculate the number of blue cars:\nBlue cars = Green cars * 3 = 10 * 3 = 30\n\nNow, we know the total number of cars is:\nTotal cars = Red + Green + Blue + Yellow\n\nWe can plug in the numbers we know into the equation to solve for the number of yellow cars:\n75 = 12 + 10 + 30 + Yellow\n\nSolving for Yellow:\nYellow = 75 - (12 + 10 + 30)\nYellow = 75 - 52\nYellow = 23\n\nSo, the rink has 23 yellow cars.'
