[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 start id=gsm8k_test_919
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 1/3 answer='To calculate the total amount raised, we first determine the profit made on each lollipop sale:\n\nProfit per lollipop = Selling price - Cost price\n                         = $0.8 - $0.5\n                         = $0.3\n\nNow, since there were 30 students and each sold 10 lollipops on average:\n\nTotal number of lollipops sold = Number of students × Number of lollipops per student\n                               = 30 × 10\n                               = 300 lollipops\n\nSo, the total profit made from selling lollipops would be:\n\nTotal profit = Total number of lollipops sold × Profit per lollipop\n              = 300 × $0.3\n              = $90\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $90 from the profit of selling lollipops.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 2/3 answer='To calculate the total amount raised from the sale of lollipops, we first need to find out how many lollipops were sold in total. Each student sold 10 lollipops at $0.8 each, so:\n\nTotal lollipops sold = Number of students × Lollipops per student\n                    = 30 × 10\n                    = 300\n\nNext, we calculate the total revenue from selling these lollipops. Since each lollipop was sold for $0.8:\n\nRevenue from lollipops = Total lollipops sold × Price per lollipop\n                      = 300 × 0.8\n                      = $240\n\nNow, we calculate the total cost of buying these lollipops. Each lollipop was bought for $0.5:\n\nCost of lollipops = Total revenue from lollipops × Cost per lollipop\n                  = $240 × 0.5\n                  = $120\n\nFinally, to find out how much money was raised from the profit of selling lollipops, we subtract the cost of buying them from the total revenue:\n\nProfit = Revenue from lollipops - Cost of lollipops\n        = $240 - $120\n        = $120\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $120 from the profit of selling lollipops.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 path 3/3 answer="To calculate the total amount raised, we first need to determine the revenue generated from selling lollipops. Each student sold 10 lollipops at $0.8 each, so the revenue from one student is:\n\n\\[ \\text{Revenue}_\\text{one\\_student} = 10 \\times \\$0.8 \\]\n\nSince there are 30 students, the total revenue from all students combined would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total\\_revenue} = 30 \\times (\\text{Revenue}_\\text{one\\_student}) \\]\n\nNext, we need to calculate the cost of buying these lollipops. Since each lollipop costs $0.5, the total cost for all lollipops would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total\\_cost} = \\text{Total\\_revenue} \\times \\$0.5 \\]\n\nFinally, to find out how much money was raised from the profit of selling lollipops, we subtract the total cost from the total revenue:\n\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = \\text{Total\\_revenue} - \\text{Total\\_cost} \\]\n\nLet's do the calculations:\n\nFirst, let's compute:\n- Revenue from one student: \\( 10 \\times \\$0.8 = \\$8 \\)\n- Total revenue from all students: \\( 30 \\times \\$8 = \\$240 \\)\n\nNext, the cost of buying lollipops:\n- Cost per lollipop: \\( \\$0.5 \\)\n- Total cost for all lollipops: \\( 30 \\times \\$0.5 = \\$15 \\)\n\nNow, the profit calculation:\n- Profit = Total revenue - Total cost\n- Profit = \\$240 - \\$15 = \\$225\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise \\$2"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 73/100 done id=gsm8k_test_919 prediction='To calculate the total amount raised, we first determine the profit made on each lollipop sale:\n\nProfit per lollipop = Selling price - Cost price\n                         = $0.8 - $0.5\n                         = $0.3\n\nNow, since there were 30 students and each sold 10 lollipops on average:\n\nTotal number of lollipops sold = Number of students × Number of lollipops per student\n                               = 30 × 10\n                               = 300 lollipops\n\nSo, the total profit made from selling lollipops would be:\n\nTotal profit = Total number of lollipops sold × Profit per lollipop\n              = 300 × $0.3\n              = $90\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $90 from the profit of selling lollipops.' gold='90' correct=False vote_counts={'To calculate the total amount raised, we first determine the profit made on each lollipop sale:\n\nProfit per lollipop = Selling price - Cost price\n                         = $0.8 - $0.5\n                         = $0.3\n\nNow, since there were 30 students and each sold 10 lollipops on average:\n\nTotal number of lollipops sold = Number of students × Number of lollipops per student\n                               = 30 × 10\n                               = 300 lollipops\n\nSo, the total profit made from selling lollipops would be:\n\nTotal profit = Total number of lollipops sold × Profit per lollipop\n              = 300 × $0.3\n              = $90\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $90 from the profit of selling lollipops.': 1, 'To calculate the total amount raised from the sale of lollipops, we first need to find out how many lollipops were sold in total. Each student sold 10 lollipops at $0.8 each, so:\n\nTotal lollipops sold = Number of students × Lollipops per student\n                    = 30 × 10\n                    = 300\n\nNext, we calculate the total revenue from selling these lollipops. Since each lollipop was sold for $0.8:\n\nRevenue from lollipops = Total lollipops sold × Price per lollipop\n                      = 300 × 0.8\n                      = $240\n\nNow, we calculate the total cost of buying these lollipops. Each lollipop was bought for $0.5:\n\nCost of lollipops = Total revenue from lollipops × Cost per lollipop\n                  = $240 × 0.5\n                  = $120\n\nFinally, to find out how much money was raised from the profit of selling lollipops, we subtract the cost of buying them from the total revenue:\n\nProfit = Revenue from lollipops - Cost of lollipops\n        = $240 - $120\n        = $120\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise $120 from the profit of selling lollipops.': 1, "To calculate the total amount raised, we first need to determine the revenue generated from selling lollipops. Each student sold 10 lollipops at $0.8 each, so the revenue from one student is:\n\n\\[ \\text{Revenue}_\\text{one\\_student} = 10 \\times \\$0.8 \\]\n\nSince there are 30 students, the total revenue from all students combined would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total\\_revenue} = 30 \\times (\\text{Revenue}_\\text{one\\_student}) \\]\n\nNext, we need to calculate the cost of buying these lollipops. Since each lollipop costs $0.5, the total cost for all lollipops would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Total\\_cost} = \\text{Total\\_revenue} \\times \\$0.5 \\]\n\nFinally, to find out how much money was raised from the profit of selling lollipops, we subtract the total cost from the total revenue:\n\n\\[ \\text{Profit} = \\text{Total\\_revenue} - \\text{Total\\_cost} \\]\n\nLet's do the calculations:\n\nFirst, let's compute:\n- Revenue from one student: \\( 10 \\times \\$0.8 = \\$8 \\)\n- Total revenue from all students: \\( 30 \\times \\$8 = \\$240 \\)\n\nNext, the cost of buying lollipops:\n- Cost per lollipop: \\( \\$0.5 \\)\n- Total cost for all lollipops: \\( 30 \\times \\$0.5 = \\$15 \\)\n\nNow, the profit calculation:\n- Profit = Total revenue - Total cost\n- Profit = \\$240 - \\$15 = \\$225\n\nTherefore, the class was able to raise \\$2": 1}
