[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the total number of Junebugs removed from Monday to Thursday:\n- Monday: 39 bugs\n- Tuesday: 2 * 39 = 78 bugs\n- Wednesday: 2 * 39 = 78 bugs\n\nAdding these together gives us the total number of bugs removed:\n39 + 78 + 78 = 205 bugs\n\nNow, we find the average number of bugs removed per day over the five days:\nTotal bugs removed = 205\nNumber of days = 5\n\nAverage number of bugs removed per day = Total bugs removed / Number of days\n= 205 / 5\n= 41 bugs per day\n\nTherefore, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 41.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 path 3/3 answer="To find the average number of Junebugs removed per day, we first need to determine the total number of Junebugs removed over the week. \n\nOn Monday, she removed 39 bugs.\nOn Tuesday and Wednesday combined, she removed \\(2 \\times 39 = 78\\) bugs each day.\nSo, for Tuesday and Wednesday combined, she removed \\(78 + 78 = 156\\) bugs.\nOn Thursday, she removed 48 bugs.\nAnd on Friday, she removed 57 bugs.\n\nNow let's sum up all the bugs removed:\n\\[39 + 156 + 48 + 57\\]\n\nCalculating the total gives us:\n\\[39 + 156 = 195\\]\n\\[195 + 48 = 243\\]\n\\[243 + 57 = 290\\]\n\nThere were 290 bugs removed in total.\n\nSince there are 7 days in a week, we divide the total by 7 to get the average daily removal:\n\\[290 \\div 7 = 41.42857...\\]\n\nRounding to the nearest whole number, the average number of Junebugs removed per day is approximately **41**."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 74/100 done id=gsm8k_test_928 prediction='233' gold='60' correct=False vote_counts={'233': 1, 'First, we calculate the total number of Junebugs removed from Monday to Thursday:\n- Monday: 39 bugs\n- Tuesday: 2 * 39 = 78 bugs\n- Wednesday: 2 * 39 = 78 bugs\n\nAdding these together gives us the total number of bugs removed:\n39 + 78 + 78 = 205 bugs\n\nNow, we find the average number of bugs removed per day over the five days:\nTotal bugs removed = 205\nNumber of days = 5\n\nAverage number of bugs removed per day = Total bugs removed / Number of days\n= 205 / 5\n= 41 bugs per day\n\nTherefore, the average number of Junebugs that Rita removes per day is 41.': 1, "To find the average number of Junebugs removed per day, we first need to determine the total number of Junebugs removed over the week. \n\nOn Monday, she removed 39 bugs.\nOn Tuesday and Wednesday combined, she removed \\(2 \\times 39 = 78\\) bugs each day.\nSo, for Tuesday and Wednesday combined, she removed \\(78 + 78 = 156\\) bugs.\nOn Thursday, she removed 48 bugs.\nAnd on Friday, she removed 57 bugs.\n\nNow let's sum up all the bugs removed:\n\\[39 + 156 + 48 + 57\\]\n\nCalculating the total gives us:\n\\[39 + 156 = 195\\]\n\\[195 + 48 = 243\\]\n\\[243 + 57 = 290\\]\n\nThere were 290 bugs removed in total.\n\nSince there are 7 days in a week, we divide the total by 7 to get the average daily removal:\n\\[290 \\div 7 = 41.42857...\\]\n\nRounding to the nearest whole number, the average number of Junebugs removed per day is approximately **41**.": 1}
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 75/100 start id=gsm8k_test_939
