[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 76/100 path 1/3 answer='To find out how many children can be in the drill, we multiply the number of rows by the number of schools in each row:\n\nNumber of rows = 7\nNumber of schools per row = 5\n\nTotal number of children = Number of rows × Number of schools per row\nTotal number of children = 7 × 5\nTotal number of children = 35\n\nSo, there will be 35 children in the drill.'
