blem, the bakery has 40 less than seven times as many loaves of bread as Sam had last Friday. So we can write:\n\n\\[ \\text{Number of loaves of bread} = 7S - 40 \\]\n\nWe know that Sam had 70 loaves of bread last Friday (since \\( S = 70 \\)). Plugging this value into our equation gives us:\n\n\\[ 7(70) - 40 = 490 - 40 = 450 \\]\n\nSo, the bakery has 450 loaves of bread.': 1}
