[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 1/3 answer='First, calculate the total area of the walls:\nNorth wall: 10 x 8 = 80 square feet\nSouth wall: 10 x 8 = 80 square feet\n\nEast wall: 5 x 8 = 40 square feet\nWest wall: 5 x 8 = 40 square feet\n\nTotal area of walls = 80 + 80 + 40 + 40 = 240 square feet\n\nNext, calculate how many gallons of paint are needed:\nGallons needed = Total area / Coverage per gallon = 240 / 20 = 12 gallons\n\nFinally, calculate the total cost:\nCost per gallon = $12\nTotal cost = Cost per gallon * Gallons needed = $12 * 12 = $144\n\nSo, it will cost $144 to paint the room.'
