[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 83/100 path 2/3 answer='Last year, there were 50 students enrolled. This year, there was a 20% increase in enrollment. To find out how many students are now enrolled, we calculate 20% of 50 and add it to the original number of students:\n\n\\( \\text{Increase} = 50 \\times \\frac{20}{100} = 50 \\times 0.2 = 10 \\)\n\nSo, the total number of students this year would be:\n\n\\( 50 + 10 = 60 \\)'
