[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 start id=gsm8k_test_1130
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many boxes of 8 crayons can be made from 200 crayons:\n\n200 crayons ÷ 8 crayons/box = 25 boxes\n\nEach box weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the boxes is:\n\n25 boxes × 8 ounces/box = 200 ounces\n\nNow, we know that each crayon weighs 1 ounce, so the total weight of the crayons is also 200 ounces.\n\nTo convert the total weight from ounces to pounds, we divide by 16 (since 1 pound = 16 ounces):\n\n200 ounces ÷ 16 ounces/pound = 12.5 pounds\n\nSo, the total weight of the crayons and the boxes is 12.5 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's calculate how many groups of 8 crayons can be made from 200 crayons:\n\n200 crayons ÷ 8 crayons/group = 25 groups\n\nEach group weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the crayons is:\n\n25 groups × 8 ounces/group = 200 ounces\n\nNow, we know that each crayon weighs 1 ounce, so the total weight of the crayons is also equal to the number of crayons multiplied by their individual weight:\n\n200 crayons × 1 ounce/crayon = 200 ounces\n\nWe're told that each box weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the boxes is:\n\n200 ounces (crayons) + 200 ounces (boxes) = 400 ounces\n\nTo convert ounces to pounds, we divide by 16 because there are 16 ounces in a pound:\n\n400 ounces ÷ 16 ounces/pound = 25 pounds\n\nSo, the total weight of the crayons and the boxes is 25 pounds."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 3/3 answer="To find the total weight of the crayons and the boxes, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. Calculate how many boxes can be filled with the crayons:\n   - Total crayons: 200\n   - Crayons per box: 8\n   - Number of boxes needed: 200 ÷ 8 = 25 boxes\n\n2. Calculate the total weight of the crayons:\n   - Weight per crayon: 1 ounce\n   - Total weight of crayons: 200 × 1 = 200 ounces\n\n3. Calculate the total weight of the boxes:\n   - Weight per box: 8 ounces\n   - Total weight of boxes: 25 × 8 = 200 ounces\n\n4. Add the total weight of the crayons and the boxes:\n   - Total weight (in ounces): 200 + 200 = 400 ounces\n\n5. Convert the total weight from ounces to pounds:\n   - There are 16 ounces in a pound\n   - Total weight in pounds: 400 ÷ 16 = 25 pounds\n\nTherefore, the total weight of the crayons and the boxes when there are 16 ounces to a pound is 25 pounds."
