[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 86/100 path 1/3 answer='First, calculate how many fish Jen gets in a month. Since there are 30 days in May, Jen will get 30 fish. Each fish eats 1 fish per day, so they eat 30 fish/day * 30 days/month = 900 fish/month.\n\nNow, since each fish needs $1 worth of food a day, Jen spends 900 fish/month * $1/fish = $900/month on food.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 86/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 86/100 path 2/3 answer='To calculate how much Jen spends on food in the month of May, we first need to determine the total number of fish she gets over the course of May. Since there are 30 days in May and she gets 3 fish each day, she will get 30 * 3 = 90 fish in total. \n\nEach fish needs $1 worth of food a day, so for 90 fish, she will need 90 * $1 = $90 worth of food in total.\n\nTherefore, Jen spends $90 on food in the month of May.'
