[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 start id=gsm8k_test_1161
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 1/3 answer="First, let's calculate how much Abraham initially had:\n\nHe owned 80 square meters of unused land.\n\nThen, he sold half of it (40 square meters) for $50 each:\n\\( 40 \\text{ m}^2 \\times \\$50/\\text{m}^2 = \\$2000 \\)\n\nAfterward, he sold another 1/4 of his land (20 square meters) for $30 each:\n\\( 20 \\text{ m}^2 \\times \\$30/\\text{m}^2 = \\$600 \\)\n\nSo far, he has made $2000 + $600 = $2600 from selling some of his land.\n\nNow, we need to find out how much he can make from selling the remaining 40 square meters at $3 per square meter:\n\\( 40 \\text{ m}^2 \\times \\$3/\\text{m}^2 = \\$120 \\)\n\nFinally, we'll add up all the earnings:\n\\( \\$2600 + \\$120 = \\$2720 \\)\n\nTherefore, Abraham will be able to earn $2720 after selling all his unused land."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate how much land Abraham sold before accounting for the additional sales:\nHalf of the land (50 square meters) was sold at $50 each, so he made 50 * 0.5 = $<<50*0.5=25>>25 from these sales.\nThen, he sold another 1/4 of the land (25 square meters) at $30 each, so he made 25 * 0.25 = $<<25*0.25=6.25>>6.25 from these sales.\nAfterward, he sold the remaining 30% of the land (24 square meters) at $3 per square meter, so he made 24 * 0.3 = $<<24*0.3=7.2>>7.2 from these sales.\nTo find out how much money Abraham can earn after selling all his unused land, we sum up the amounts from each sale: $25 + $6.25 + $7.2 = $<<25+6.25+7.2=48.45>>48.45.\nTherefore, Abraham will be able to earn $48.45 after selling all his unused land.'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 3/3 answer="First, let's determine how much land Abraham sold:\n- He sold half of the land, so he sold \\( \\frac{80}{2} = 40 \\) square meters.\n- After a month, he sold another \\( \\frac{1}{4} \\) of the land, so he sold \\( \\frac{80}{4} = 20 \\) square meters.\n\nNow we can calculate the total amount of money he made from each sale:\n- For the first sale: \\( 40 \\times \\$50 = \\$2000 \\)\n- For the second sale: \\( 20 \\times \\$30 = \\$600 \\)\n\nFinally, we sum up the amounts from both sales to find out how much money he made in total:\n\\( \\$2000 + \\$600 = \\$2600 \\)\n\nSo, Abraham will be able to earn $2600 after selling all his unused land."
