[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 91/100 path 3/3 answer="To find out how many pomelos Eve gave away, we first calculate what fraction of the original amount she had. She started with 20 pomelos and ended up with 1/4 of them. So, the fraction of the original amount she had left is 1/4. To find out how many pomelos that is, we multiply the total number of pomelos by this fraction:\n\nFraction given away = (1/4) * 20\n\nNow, let's do the calculation:\nFraction given away = 20 / 4\nFraction given away = 5\n\nSo, Eve gave away 5 pomelos."
