[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 94/100 path 2/3 answer='First, calculate the total amount of dog food consumed by the German Shepherds in one day:\n3 German Shepherds * 5 kg/day = 15 kg/day\n\nNext, calculate the total amount of dog food consumed by the Bulldogs in one day:\n2 Bulldogs * 3 kg/day = 6 kg/day\n\nNow, add the two amounts together to find out how much dog food is consumed in one day:\n15 kg/day (German Shepherds) + 6 kg/day (Bulldogs) = 21 kg/day\n\nTo find out how much dog food they will need in a week, multiply the daily consumption by 7 days:\n21 kg/day * 7 days = 147 kg/week\n\nTherefore, the Kennel House will need 147 kilograms of dog food in a week.'
