[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 95/100 path 2/3 answer="First, let's identify the ages of the siblings:\n- The older brother is 12 years old.\n- The younger brother is also 12 years old (since they are the same age).\n- There are 3 sisters, each 16 years old.\n\nNow, let's calculate the total age of all the siblings:\n- The older brother + Younger brother + 3 sisters = 12 + 12 + 3 * 16 = 12 + 12 + 48 = 72 years.\n\nSo, the total age of all these siblings is 72 years."
