ermine how far Aaron ran. Since he runs each mile twice as fast as Vanessa, and Vanessa ran 4 miles, Aaron would have run \\(4 \\times 2 = 8\\) miles. \n\nNow, we know that Aaron took 16 minutes to complete his part of the race. To find out how long it takes Vanessa to complete her part, we divide the time Aaron took by the number of miles he ran:\n\n\\[ \\text{Time for Vanessa} = \\frac{\\text{Time taken by Aaron}}{\\text{Distance Aaron ran}} = \\frac{16}{8} = 2 \\text{ minutes} \\]\n\nTherefore, Vanessa took 2 minutes to complete her part of the race.": 1, 'To find out how long it took Vanessa to complete her part of the race, we first need to determine how far Aaron ran. Since Aaron runs each mile twice as fast as Vanessa, and Vanessa runs 4 miles, Aaron would have run:\n\n\\[ 4 \\text{ miles} \\times 2 = 8 \\text{ miles} \\]\n\nNow, we know that Aaron completed his part of the race in 16 minutes. To find out how long it took Vanessa to complete her part, we divide the time it took Aaron by 2 (since he ran at twice the speed):\n\n\\[ \\frac{16 \\text{ minutes}}{2} = 8 \\text{ minutes} \\]\n\nSo, Vanessa took 8 minutes to complete her part of the race.': 1}
