[self_consistency][qwen2_5_0_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 100/100 path 2/3 answer='First, we calculate the discounted price of the radiator:\nDiscounted price = Original price - Discount amount\n                  = $400 - (80% of $400)\n                  = $400 - ($400 * 0.8)\n                  = $400 - $320\n                  = $80\n\nNext, we calculate the total cost of hiring the mechanic:\nTotal cost = Cost per hour * Number of hours\n            = $50 * 3\n            = $150\n\nFinally, we add up all the costs:\nTotal cost = Cost of radiator + Cost of mechanic\n           = $80 + $150\n           = $230\n\nTherefore, Mark paid a total of $230.'
